name: Brewery Park at Tumwater Falls (formerly Tumwater Falls Park)
address: 110 Deschutes Way SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
This is an interesting park with more than just a beautiful walk along the river. Don’t miss the fish ladders, the bridge to a closer view of the historic brewery, and take a picnic so the kids can play hard at the playground. 
If eating out is more your style you are in LUCK! Eat at The Falls Terrace restaurant, a local favorite. The views are impressive but the place is full of family charm. 
While this park is a great spot to bring your out of state company, it’s a local favorite!
There’s quite a bit of construction going on now so 4 stars- but when the trail is complete and other improvements done- I’ll be back to update.

Lots to look at here! There is a fish hatchery (still under construction) that will be amazing. Trails are well maintained and there is an area set aside for native plants. Informative kiosks add to the experience.

I have always loved the falls, I have been taking my children there since they were babies, they are now 36 and down. I absolutely love the new upcoming  improvements, so excited for the new fish hatchery!  That will be so fascinating and exciting to watch!

Any time of year, Tumwater Falls is a wonderful place for a walk.  Today, even with the salmon gone and extensive construction going on, my guests and I still enjoyed the fabulous beauty of the Falls, with the moss covered rocks, which are like sculpture from years of tumbling water.  My (grown) daughter and I have even decided to come  every 3 months, each time she visits.  We love it that much.

And during the salmon run, it's an unforgettable experience - like my first time there.  :~]

This place is so nice to go to always. I really love waterfalls, just something about them is so soothing. It's a great place to take senior photos or prom photos. The trails they have their are nice as well.

name: Priest Point Park
address: 2600 East Bay Drive Northeast, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: I have been coming to this park for years. It is a great place to run on the trails, walk your dog, or take your kids to play and explore. My wife and I got married in the historic rose garden. Very good memories here. Please go visit soon. You will not regret it!

Excellent trail network. Well maintained and only a couple of places that get steep, but stairs are there to keep footing even. In general a bit technical and easy/medium difficulty.

Many interesting sights to see in this park: bridges, a bay, birds.
We always love walking the trails at Priest Point with Buddha (our Springer Spaniel)! Always find them in great condition and well manicured, plus, definitely some of the best sunset views around!

Loved the trails and the size in general, it's beautiful and there's so much to do. Bring your kids to play at the play area, have a birthday party play at the beach area hike with your dog or s/o .... It's one of my favorite parks of Olympia period

Great trails for all levels of hiking or just plain walking. There are trails on both sides of the bridge that you can cross over to. Wish there were more documented trails but if you got the time go take an adventure.

name: Percival Landing Park
address: 217 Thurston Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Great sight seeing that makes you think "wow, I live here". 
..just don't turn around and notice all the issues the city has right now

I come to Olympia about once a month, and this was the first time I made time to come to the waterfront. I'm glad I did, and if you come, you will enjoy a nice walk, stunning views of the water (I bet it's even better with better weather), and that marvelous feel of being by the sea. So many boats moored here, I got some great pictures. I'll come back, for sure.
Nice area with lots to see but expect to meet all ☆sORTs☆ of people wanting something you may or may not have.
Love to come down here for pokemoning. Can be a bit crowded at times but overall it is a lovely place for a walk by the water.
I love walking along this waterfront. The boats are very iconic. Plus the playground has enough to keep the kids busy and the bathrooms are clean and well-lit.

name: Hands On Children's Museum
address: 414 Jefferson St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: So much stuff to do! I don't think kids will ever want to leave! The activities are educational, great for a field trip. There are many activities that use imaginations, such as the "food" area where there is plastic foods that you can "cook." I recommend going here.

Awesome place to bring kids of all ages. There is always some educational activity going on. It can get pretty busy and crowded on event days so its good to get there earlier or later, but not at the peak times on weekends. Parking in the back can get a little crazy. There is so much to do and even a few water based activities. When the weather is warm, there's a bunch of outside areas set up too.

This is really a neat learning environment for kids of all ages. We were happy to get a membership after our initial visit, but have regretted getting it ever since. Here's why: The problem is they have no limit on capacity numbers and it often gets way too overcrowded to enjoy anything. It basically becomes a Hunger Games-esque environment where it's every kid for themselves and they have to fight to get to explore anything. Additionally, there are several exhibits that don't have working buttons or fully functioning displays. Makes it quite disappointing. What are we paying for? Lastly, they never turn away visibly sick children! So, until they decide to monitor their capacity levels, fix ALL the broken buttons & displays, and refuse entry to visibly sick children we won't be back.

This place is a wonderful museum in WA. It blows away the Seattle and Bellevue ones as well. The team is constantly cleaning and tidying up play areas to help keep the experience meaningful for the kids. Beautiful outdoor play area as well and a great cafe. Lots of parking too. The membership is worth it.
My children spent a few good hours loving the fun filled adventures this facility had in store for them. Much fun. Many recommends. A

name: WET Science Center
address: 500 Adams St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: We love going here! Great FREE programming for young people.  My son loves playing in the main area and has benefited from multiple programs held here on Saturdays.  The people working here are very kind and helpful.  Highly recommend.

Awesome Staff! Great learning stations & activities for children! I had my 6y.o. Granddaughter & my 10 y.o. Grandson for the Weekend of 7/26-7/28/2019, we saw this place on the way to somewhere else and opted to go check out the Wet Science Center. My Grandbabies COULDN'T get enough of the Scavenger Hunt. We had did some cool artwork & before I knew it they had left the classroom rushing back to do more at one of the learning stations. 👏👏👏👍Kudos & Thanks so much for putting a smile on our faces. I love seeing children enjoy learning experiences.

Staff is very professional, yet consice and clear. Cool hands on projects and tons of information. I enjoyed myself there, so if you haven't gone, take the whole family, all ages can enjoy this space, and give yourself at least an hour to explore.  And it's free!
Fun place for adults and kids. The best part is that it is free! They often have special events on Saturday. There is also a tour of the plant each quarter.
The gift that keeps on giving, and it's such a beautiful Jewel of Olympia, you must visit, you will not be disappointed.

name: Marathon Park
address: 1011 Deschutes Pkwy SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Great place to walk or run and think about anything. Bathrooms are usually clean. And only because they work hard to keep them that way. I just wish the water was cleaner. It would be nice to sit here and watch the kids fish. But still the best place to see the city at night with the lights dancing off the water.
Excellent place for a jog. Well maintained, year round bathrooms and free parking in 2 lots.

Great place for a walk, run, and all sorts of fun. Bring your dog, your kid, your wife, anyone. Don't be afraid to make eye contact with strangers and say hello. You might make a friend! You'll never know unless you go, yo.

Small grassy area with a few picnicking tables over looking Capitol Lake and the Capitol Building. No bbq or grills so if you want to eat her bring food.

Restrooms open till dusk. And is the start of a walking/jogging trail around lake. Ample parking, no gate at night well lit lot. The walking bridge is beautiful and runs parallel to the old railway bridge. 

In springtime at night you can enjoy the local brown bag population.

Nice, clean walking trail, with switch backs that go up to the Capitol campus. There is a lot of foot traffic there, so it feels safe to walk, if you're alone.  Great view from all locations, too! There are clean restrooms on either side of the Lake.

name: West Bay Park
address: 700 W Bay Dr NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Beautiful peaceful place to take  a moment to yourself or to get out for a walk with family and friends. I love how it was created for a peaceful place for people in the community to go and  enjoy themselves and  have the opportunity to meet new people... intentions were great when they made this park.... i love how there is a little spot for the kids to be able to be down on the beach like area and be able to touch the Puget sound.

West Bay Park is a small, relaxed park. Its a good place to walk or play with your active dog and it provides a good view of the bay. I recommend dressing warmly because it always has a breeze no matter the weather, though this could be nice in the summer.

Beautiful! I hadn't been to Oly for about a decade, so I never got to be on this side of the docks. Visited my best friend and had a wonderful time looking at all the crabs, barnacles, and ducks. I'll definitely be back!

It was a beautiful overcast morning but everything was calm and peaceful. The park was well maintained and clean. The Rotary club provided a very nice lookout area, which is where I stood to take these photos.
Clean and super beautiful. Nice little place to bring the pup and play with some baby crabs near the water.

name: Washington State Capitol Building and Campus
address: 416 Sid Snyder Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98504, USA
reviews: Had a really excellent experience checking out this place. There was so much beauty everywhere, and the architecture was amazing. The immense size of the main building blew me away. There is lots of room to sit down on all the grass lawns, and there is a beautiful fountain. I highly recommend checking out this place if you're visiting the area, you won't regret it! Super fascinating.

Thank you, for giving me hope! Beyond the untruths and slanderous guessing, I have met you. Up close and personal I have learned about character that earned you stay in this place. The love of America, strength in a united family, and humility endures. Faithfulness to our higher power also makes you my neighbor. Thank you, for helping build a future for us all.

+ The benefits from time in a conservatory greenhouse helps!
So I was able to have a platform to speak out when nobody else would Lewis County...

Oh man this was a perfect little stop for my wife’s and I. On our way way from Portland to Seattle, we said hey let’s stop here and it turned out to be perfect. The free tour was great and the tour guide very very knowledgeable! And of course the architecture inside the building was beautiful. A must see if you’re around the area!

The Capitol building is a short walk from the visitor center parking lot. Very welcoming personnel and docents enhanced the visit. The extensive use of marble from five countries is astounding. Our docent was a former educator and extremely knowledgeable. Although there weren’t any sessions underway, we enjoyed seeing the areas and learning more about government processes. The rotunda and the unique Tiffany chandeliers are exquisite. Even if you don’t “need to go”, go into one of the restrooms for more marble craftsmanship. If you’re able, take the stairs for even more. There is a small cafeteria where you can get a beverage and food, but it is also used by employees. We went in late morning for a beverage before our tour but decided to pass due to the wait and our approaching tour time. I can imagine that during lunch, you might have a wait because many menu items are prepared as they are ordered. Fortunate for us, we visited on Potato Day. Staff and visitors were treated in the rotunda to complementary baked potatoes with numerous toppings to choose from plus beverages. We were told that the following day would be Ice Cream Day. Although there were four adults and no children on my guided tour, I did see materials designed for children and got a sense that the tour could easily be adapted to interest them

name: LBA Park
address: 3333 Morse-Merryman Rd SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: I always love going here. I like that they keep up to date on everything there. Something that I found out a while back is that this park is much bigger than it appears. They have these trails in the forest then we found the actual property marker of the park. It was a pretty cool experience. I definitely recommend you check out those cool trails.

Great park. Awesome playground with a zipline. Small kids and big kids areas. Covered picnic area. Sports fields. Walking trail that connects to forested trails. Two parking lots. But the larger lot had had trouble with burglary.
What a fun park for kids! All kinds of great pieces of playground equipment and softball field. Beautifully kept grounds and walking trails.
One of the best parks in the Olympia area with scenic trails, play ground, bike path and kids play yard. This park is for everyone from senior citizen to kidd since all of them can have fun here.
It's very natural. Love the many trail's that are available

name: Port Plaza
address: 701 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: LOVE the atmosphere! Reminds me of some of the warfs in San Francisco.

I was there for Olympia Harbor days, which is always fun. A lot of vendors, boats you can tour and food to eat. When nothing is going on, its still a nice place to take a walk, theres a playground along the way for the kids and food along the way too. It's a nice play to take in some of Olympia.
Lots of festivals in the summertime.  Beautiful area.  Parking can be challenging which is why I gave 4 out of 5 stars.
Always a great romantic walk on the good ol' Olympia waterfront.

Always love coming downtown Olympia and the Waterfront is one of our favorite stops this park is always clip kept really clean and they often have events of some sort or possibly a festival we stumbled across the Wooden Boat Festival on this particular visit there's lots of parking around near as well as the farmers market is a close walk so you can do everything at once a great place to spend a few hours wandering around with beautiful scenery

name: Yauger Park
address: 3100 Capital Mall Dr SW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Big well maintained park. Bathrooms, shelter area, trail, nature preserve, large playground and community garden. Theres a lot of homeless attracted to this area unfortunately, which can make you want to stay a little closer to the kiddos

A one size fits all park. The parks and rec. Service staff are great. The ball fields are well done, as well as the 22 shoe pits.. the one missing things are parking in surrounding communies so the Senior pro shoe players can park 5th wheels, the prides Tripp. Half pipe , so skilled skateboard can stop playing in the swimming pool. Lastly the hanging gardens and running Creek into and out of the park . The parks and rec are, I say again great and the community is blessed...
I love doing my daily walks here with the family. Also has a lot of poke stops for pokemon go and a gym which makes the walk fun for everyone
I love this Park! Wonderful pond-things, ducks, ball fields, playground, restrooms, and tons of space. Great for a relaxing afternoon walk!
Really nice park with lots of shade on a hot day!

name: Heritage Park Fountain
address: 330 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Super fun place for kiddos to play! Love the Capitol building in the background!  There’s lots of variety in the water splashing and even music/sounds off and on.  Benches need some repairing but plenty of grass and shade to sit in... would be nice to have restrooms nearby but can find those at the Park a few blocks away.

I used to LOVE this splash pad and park but the day this photo was taken there was a bizarre fight/altercation and about 3 (adult) people were bathing and washing their clothes (and shoes) in the water where all the children were playing.  I don't know how I feel about that, but I have suggestions for the City: Clean up the damn park. Make it usable for tax paying citizens. Hire a guard or rent a cop to walk the grounds, fix the damn benches (seriously!) and keep the place tidy.  I recognize we have a homelessness issue and a drug addiction issue, but letting this park go to the wayside is only going to make it worse.
I find that watching this fountain dance and watching the people play around it is a great way to clear my mind snd put me in a great mood. There have been times I have come here just to fo that.
I love going to Heritage Park to do my thinking and crocheting and coloring
It was great. Really nice on a hot day!

name: Wonderwood Park
address: 5304 32nd Ave SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: I love this park. It's huge and has 2 park sections. One section has smaller big toys and has a little mini 1 hoop basketball area. I love going to this part, it's more secluded. The other section has much bigger big toys. I like the new stuff they put in it. Love the musical toys, it's so creative. They have lots of trails that you can walk through that all connect to each section. They also have a paved trail that connects the two park sections to each other. They have a tennis court. They have a full on basketball court at the bigger section. They have picnic table areas for eating. They have a covered area for eating like if you want to have a big group there. This is one of my favorite parks and always holds wonderful memories for me.
Very pretty park! Well kept and the trails are so pretty and decently shaded for hot days! Good trail to bring family or dogs.

This is a fun park.  We went in the morning and the shade was perfect.  I enjoyed how the play structure was nestled among trees.  Basketball courts, ball fields, and lots more.  Great walking trails as well.

I ADORE this gorgeous park.  Never too many other ppl here and i always feel closer to my Higher Power walking amid the huge wonderful trees on the trails here.  Plus, periodically, the awesome folks from the Lacey Rocks hide the neatest painted rocks all over here and its like an unexpected easter egg hunt... SO FUN!! ❤

Love this park. It's well kept and has a variety of activity to fit everyone in the family, no matter the age. Bathroom is clean. Has a few picnic areas, some more private than others. The walking trail is beautiful.

name: Bigelow House Museum
address: 918 Glass Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: Lots of great history , Ron was an awesome tour guide! Amazing pieces of art throughout the house
Amazing, peaceful and clean place

This was the first home built in Washington that was not a log cabin. It was built by Harvard alum, Daniel Bigelow around 1852 after he arrived in the area by crossing the Oregon Trail. After he married, he and his wife had 8 children and hosted a few important historical figures such as Susan B. Anthony. Mrs. Bigelow was very active in the women's suffrage movement. The house was added onto during the several years it remained in the Bigelow family or 1994. It became a state house museum shortly before that even when the last of the family was living there. Cheryl, our docent, was extremely knowledgeable and thorough. The tour lasts about an hour and is well worth the time. They only ask for donations; there is no set entrance fee.

We were amazed at how many unusual historical objects they showed us as well as all we learned of the Bigelows and early Olympia. Imagine my surprise to discover this place when we moved here this year...my ancient kin...I am related back to 1620 or so...near as I can determine. I came away feeling very proud of this part of the family too!! They sound much like my side of the clan too...and it is a very well preserved place compared to others of like age we have seen in recent years. Highly recommend a visit here.
Great place to learn about early Olympia Washington.

name: East Bay Public Plaza
address: 325 Marine Dr NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Great place for family and or solo people!
Awesome place to get wet.  Kid friendly stream of water.
The creek was a ton of fun. An Olympia treasure, and highly recommended destination for parents and children.

This place is awesome! Perfect for toddlers on a hot day. Feels like being at a real stream, without any of the danger! There’s even bathrooms nearby, and a security guard who walks the perimeter. The way it’s landscaped, you really don’t feel like you’re in the middle of the city. And right next door to an awesome children’s museum if you need something else to do! Wish you could park longer than 3 hrs on the street though. :(

It's nice, but the white haired elderly security guard is a jerk and will stare you down and follow you around like a criminal if you have a vape in your pocket. He gave me the creeps, wasn't doing anything wrong. Didn't vape around kids. +the kids museum was closed already and no kids around. Be warned the vape police will be on your tail if you have one.

And for the record, there were no signs anywhere in this plaza saying that you could not smoke or vape there. So if that's the rule they need to get some damn signs saying so.

name: Puget Sound Estuarium
address: 309 State Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Nice place great for the kid's to visit and learn about our sea and marine life we have in our beautiful city.

Saltwater tanks and Estuary education! A wonderful place for children and scientist of all ages too. Look for the Discovery Speaker Talks during the fall/winter for additional Puget Sound Science Education at LOTT.
So fun, can't wait to go back even he's a bit bigger
Staff was super friendly and the content is really educational! Small but cheap and several stations for kids to be entertained.
Fall thru on a weekend between 11am and 4ish pm for some awesome hands on exhibits, live marine life and informative chats with interpreters. A must see if you're in the OLY/TAC area

name: Capitol Lake Park
address: 5th Ave SW &, Water St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Beautiful view, walk, bike ride, etc. Easy to access find. Spring has beautiful trees around. At night, the capital lights up
It was beautiful! The water isn't very safe so don't go in! But my baby brother was very excited to see the ducks :) Its a really beautiful place so don't forget to check it out.

It is a good place for visitors to stop-by.

There is trail available on the perimeter of the lake for people who want to spend more time. 

Washington State Capitol Building is also visible from the lake

One of my favorite parts of downtown. Great loop trail around the lake. Plenty of spots to just sit and enjoy a beautiful day, on the grass or on a bench. Fall is the best, the trees lining the lake just burst with color. Great views of the capitol and some fresh air when you need to step out of downtown.

This is one of the best places in Olympia to hang out and just relax. It overlooks a number of boats in the marina, so there’s definitely a majestic feel when you’re crossing by the bridge or passing through. I’ve even seen a number of seals on occasion which is pretty cool for just a park in the middle of the city

name: Tumwater Historical Park
address: 802 Deschutes Way SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Fun park with river side view of the old Olympia Brewery.  This is one of those parks that for whatever reason the playground usually has more parents than children.  There are walking trails and covered areas.  Can get busy at times, but worth the visit.
This park is great since it's updating. Kids love. The zip line is very popular

Nice park. Part of it is wild with dirt paths. The kept up grass areas are very nice with interpretive history displays. Not nearly as impressive as the Falls park next door, but it is pretty and had a lot of additional history of the area on its displays.

I love this place! Even when its crazy with a ton of people it's fun. The park is huge and worth a visit. Huge covered area, real bathrooms, good amount of parking, and fun for all. The only thing that could make this place literally perfect would be a baby swing!
Amazing playground, and a great walking trail. The views along the water are nice. We saw tons of waterfowl and a bald eagle! Lots of Pokemon Go and Wizards Unite locations. :)

name: Yashiro Japanese Garden
address: 1010 Plum St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: I've been there and it was beautiful but today, Saturday, at noon it was closed but the sign said Dawn to dusk

This Japanese garden is small, pretty and FREE entry. It has koi fishes in a pond and a very small waterfall. It is next to a busy road, so not zen unless you wear headphones and listen to instrumental music. 
Otherwise, worth a visit if you’re in the area.

This is a cute city park. It's very small. Parking is a challenge as the lot is small. The paths are lined with flowers and the pond is very nice. The park is well maintained and clean. The spring flowers were just in bloom. I hoped to see a Sakura in bloom... there were some across the street.

All the plants that were there were beautiful, but lacked in variety. Lots of the same bamboo and pine trees. And the koi pond was pretty stagnant. Lots of coins in the water, a little bit of trash and only one little fish that just wanted to hide by the waterfall.
Cute little park. Small and appeared well kept.

name: Schmidt House
address: 330 Schmidt Pl SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Bob Crims private group tours are wonderful, with 60 years working on site, there's potential for a new story every visit. The building is beautiful and full of local history.
Fun day with the family
My wife and I got married here in 2008 so it holds a special place in our hearts. Great staff and a great venue for events.
Beautiful venue but staff is cranky and unwilling to help.
Nice place for events and weddings.  Nice rose garden.

name: Bigelow Park
address: 1220 Bigelow Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews:
I have been going here since I was a baby (1990) and it is always so quiet. I have never once been where it was crowded. I love that they have a squishy rubber type floor under the play equipment. I don't worry as much about my daughter falling or tripping as I would with rocks or bark. The play equipment is appropriate for a large age range as well which is great. Many parks cater to either younger or older kids it seems and have little of one or the other.

 I have many great memories here. Though it is small, it is nice. There is however occasionally someone smoking pot or cigarettes too near the play area which isn't cool. That is never really a problem, though since we could always go explore the trees and stone structure off to the side.
Nice park. I don't have anything really bad or good to say about bigalow. Nice place to take nature photos.
Always busy with lots of neighborhood kids, and there are fun toys to play on... I love the flooring they use at the park, its so soft to walk on!
Beautiful little park! Very remote but still a nice place to visit
Wide open park in residential setting. Nice to live nearby and have access by walking. Gotta watch out for the druggies in the parking lot like every city park though

name: Kettle View Park
address: 1250 Eagle Bend Dr SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Lots of covered areas a nice tennis court plus a soccer field
I nice small park with good big toys. Entertaining for toddlers and bigger kids
Nice little neighborhood park!

Nice park for dog walking. Has a bathroom and a drinking fountain.  Also has a second path that connects for an extended walk behind the duplexes and a path that connects to another neighborhood where you can then walk to Barclift park. Love it here! Be really glad when the construction of apartments is done the noise is awful and disrupts the peace at the park.
Awesome little park!

name: Watershed Park
address: 2500 Henderson Blvd SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Beautiful Park. This is the park I was proposed to. Will always remember this park and I've got beautiful pictures from here. We come back every year on our anniversary. ❤️
Awesome park! Even in December its kinda warm. They have like 20 little bridges over the creek and the trail is maintained by volunteers and they do a great job!

Beautiful park with looping trails and multiple entry points. Leisurely walk with the dogs (leashed, of course) provided a nice little workout while enjoying the magnificent wonders of nature. Enhanced by a long time friend who I rather see these days.
Great tail. Over a 3 mile long loop, with multiple exit points. Lot's of moss and little streams.
Fairly accessible and à beautiful well kept area. Will be back for some trail running!

name: Olympic Flight Museum
address: 7637 Old Hwy 99 SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Great place to visit. The staff is very friendly and knowledgeable about all aircraft. They have plenty of stories to talk about. Volunteers are welcome. The air show is yearly in the summer. Open Tuesday through Friday 11-5 closed on Monday. They sometimes have special events. Book a wedding. The gift shop is pretty good

Located at Olympia Airport. Parking out front. Mostly tended by volunteers. Interesting hangar with local nostalgia. A lot of work has gone into establishing this facility so drop by and drop in a donation. Enjoy a step back into history before we lose it.

Great place to take the kids. It's small with only about a dozen aircraft. Lots of information and artifacts. There are two aircraft kids can climb into and around. There is also a mock control panel us use. Good customer service with a variety of discounted entry fees. Unisex restroom on site. Nice little store with something to interest most. Easy access and exit from the primary road.

Docent was amazing spending time with our 12 year old grandsons explaining things.  Several aircraft for kids to climb in and experience.   Interesting displays along the walls to.look at.  A small museum, but well worth the visit
Amazing exhibits and displays. 3 aircraft on site which you can climb in and get up close and personal with.

name: Rainier Vista Community Park
address: 5475 45th Ave SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: Nice park, it's pretty huge, has a large parking lot, and has a lot of things to use such as: playground area, basketball court, tennis court, baseball fields, soccer fields, skate park, and restrooms. Tons of open grass to utilize for volleyball nets or whatever you feel like using the open area for. There are a few gazebos and picnic tables as well, and a few park benches. Very few shaded areas though, not a whole lot of trees, so if you want shade then definitely bring your giant umbrellas or canopy's.

3 sandy volleyball courts, 3 baseball diamonds, gihugic soccer area, kids' playground, 2 tracks, tennis courts, baskbetball... and an amazing skate park. Also drinking fountains & restrooms, and plenty of parkung. I don' even know what else, but what more could ya' ask for from a park that isn't on a lake and isn't a theme park other than what a lotta' kids call "Skate Park"? I'm told they even had a great fireworks display ( that I missed ).
Wide open spaces accomodating many sports.  Paved trails for long walks and grassy areas, playgrounds and space for kids to run.  Plenty of parking.  I've never felt unsafe here.
Beautiful park with lots of amenities. We took engagement photos this weekend and there was unlimited locations for fantastic shots!
Such a nice park to have a get together. We had a cousins birthday here and it was peaceful and beautiful. Didn't see and bums hanging out was the best part!

name: Woodland Creek Community Park
address: 6729 Pacific Ave SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: It was very exciting my grandson is almost two and the slides and play equipment was perfect for his age. They also have more stuff for older kids. One thing I didn't like was that they have bark for the ground so my grandson got slivers in his hand I wish that they had foam padding. We even got to see the Canadian geese.

This community park has a very pretty little lake(Long's Pond), with migratory birds, fishing, BBQ areas, kids play areas, and level walking loops.   Swimming and boating are not allowed.

There is a very tidy community meeting hall that can be rented for parties, memorials, etc.

Parking:  Free and ample.

This park is really neat. There is a big playground good for little and big kids, pond to feed ducks and geese, gazebo to sit under, community center, disk golf and trails to walk around. We took 6 kids ages 3-17 and had a blast. We even did some geocaching. Definitely will be back to this one.

We attended the Lacey Fish-In at the lake here.  It was rainy but we had a fantastic time.  Fun park!  We were successful in catching a fish and would have stayed for longer if it wasn’t raining.  We will be back as we enjoyed our time here.

So much to see and do.The llake for fishing all the room for running and great play structures. Covered tables for picnicking and benches to set and watch your children play. I just wish there were more swings ,children love to swing and it is very good for their emtions there is only like 2 swings there.

name: West Central Park
address: 1919 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Stunning example of what a dedicated group of community builders can accomplish with vision & grit.
Building heart into the community.
Amazing community park. Dang good vibes.
Nice little park. It is very small, but well maintained. There is also an area with a stage where people can perform. I love waking here with the dogs.
I go to relax it great

name: Pioneer Park
address: 5801 Henderson Blvd SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Lovely beaches and access to the river, there's a few different spots and they are all quite nice! It can be a bit cold but it's definitely worth a trip on a warmer day!
One of my favorite parks of all time.

Great to have a place that's close where the whole family can get out and appreciate some of the things we have in our own back yards. The river was refreshing with the heat, there's enough space for everyone without disturbing families or other people around you, and more importantly, the people were great and well behaved. My daughter loves it there and we will definitely be returning.

I love this park because there are nice walking trails, its clean, and easy access to the river. Its a great place to go with kids to float in the summer! It takes about an hour the water is very mellow so you dont have to stress to much about anything bad happening.
Cute park, with scenic trails. There are bathrooms, a playground, a volleyball area, and a baseball field. There is plenty of space to spread out/run around. Great place to walk your dog or hangout.

name: Woodard Bay Conservation Area
address: Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: We were invited out for an afterwork walk by friends and it was a wonderful experience. The trail is a gentle slope up a hill and the crest overlooks a lovely scenic view of the bay with two separate viewing areas a few dozen yards apart. It's a lovely, well maintained path and winds through some gorgeous greenery. I highly recommend for a short walk with a small group.
Absolutely beautiful. Great place. Love to come and just clear my head. My kids also love it here. I think i also want yo go kayaking soon.

This place has always been a family favorite! All year round! 

The paved pathway makes it perfect for wheelchair access, and the hiking trail is awesome too! Bathrooms are at the end of the trail. Bring a snack, and always pick up your trash. 

Come in late summer to see the bats 🦇 fly out from the old rail road ties.
Awesome and unique all in one.  Bats spend the warmer months in an old railroad bridge.  Seals can often be seen.  Boat ramp if you kayak/canoe.  Beautiful.  Thank you.
beautiful area, nice Trail. Nice time of year to be out here watching all the seals and a large variety of birds

name: Sylvester Park
address: 615 Washington St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: This is such a nice quiet peaceful place a great spot to eat lunch.

This is a great space in the city, downtown and close to the state Capitol, and you will enjoy the space.  It’s also recommended because it is not filled with people experiencing homelessness.  Lots of great restaurants around for a quick lunch or dinner.

Olympia WA does not disappoint!  We went out from the hotel to walk the dog and heard music . . . Orchestra music . . . Phantom of the Opera music!  We walked to the park and found the amazing Music in the Park!  What an amazing city!  Beauty, Culture and Class! Wish we could stay!
Very pretty park with the beautiful old capital building. Unfortunately there were a lot of homeless people sleeping there now unlike when I have been there in the past.

With an absolutely gorgeous state building overlooking it, Sylvester Park is a beautiful little nook to go to in the middle of downtown. The grass is well kept and the squirrels are entertaining to watch. The only downfall is the traffic around it and the number of people that set up camp there for various reasons (although they tend to keep to themselves, it can be a bit crowded at times). From time to time, they have small events there at the gazebo in the center of the park which are amusing to attend, although parking can be scarce so be ready for a short jaunt from your car to get to the park.

name: Friendly Grove Park
address: 2316 Friendly Grove Rd NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: Cute neighborhood place to spend the afternoon. Clean! Let's keep it that way. People are nice to each other there. Perfect for family or walking your dog in the morning.
Very Cool little park with nice walkways, playground, small skate park, basketball half court, soccer nets and more! My daughter Kk, son Wesley and I just got done playing here and it was great!

Lovely park for everyone in the community. Dog friendly, with play areas for children, and picnicking areas to enjoy the well manicured lawns. Tennis courts also available for your volleying pleasure.

A nice family park with kid's playground equipment and nearby restrooms. Plenty of places to walk around. They have a large house-like place to rent for special occasions that is quite large with plenty of room in the grassy area to have many tents and tables to seat and entertain your guests.
Pretty park, especially great for younger kids and toddlers

name: Lions Park
address: 800 Wilson St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: There are a couple of things, like a rock to climb, for my older kids and they still have stuff for my babies!
Perfect place to do and eat lunch. I loved sound the corner got several years and would bring the dog and play fetch for hours at the baseball diamond. The upgrades are amazing too

This is a real centerpiece of the neighborhood. I remember growing up playing YMCA sports on these fields as a kid and now I'm seeing people my age with their own kids playing around on those same fields. It's kept up pretty well by the city. Has a nice playground for kids to mess around on and a covered bench area for a picnic or even a birthday party in the summer!

Cute little neighborhood park in a great community. A fun playground for different developmental levels, a mini spray area to keep cool on hot days, tennis court, basketball hoop, a little baseball field and covered picnic area as well as quite a few picnic tables dispersed.
Lions park is a nice little spot to hang out and have a picnic. The facilities in this park include permanent restrooms, a covered area with tables, a fenced tennis court and parking.

name: Grass Lake Nature Reserve
address: 814 Kaiser Rd NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: I took my 4 grandchildren ages 12 to 5.  The walk was easy and we saw so many plants, berries, flowers, trees.  The kids loved the quiet.  They particularly liked finding the water.

I enjoyed this excellent urban ramble in the woods. The beginning and end of the mile and a half Loop trail is an open Prairie. The remainder of it was Forest and it was beautiful. I was there on a beautiful cloudless day birding and enjoyed the cool cover of the forest canopy. I didn't get a look at the lake nearby, but the underbrush was pretty thick and I couldn't maneuver and close enough.
It's a beautiful clean park. Great for dog walks

It was beautiful aside from the pile of old bones at the beginning of the trail. If they have history I would like an informational plaque stating such. If it's illegal or unsafe I would like it removed. The lack of trail markers also confuses me it feels like I might walk into someone's backyard.

Quick loop takes less than half hour to walk. Very flat. The forest if pleasant and feels secluded. No major views of the water as there is no real shoreline. However there are places you can see it if you follow some of the side trails. It's a good place to run in the summer. During winter the exposed tree roots are a bit hazerdous for running, at least for me.

name: Tolmie State Park
address: 7730 61st Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews:
Another great State Park in Wa State!

This park has wooded hills that roll down to the rocky beach. Trails cut through the woods and follow some of the tributaries as they cut through the woods heading out to the sound. See this park on high tide and low tide as the experience is a little different for each!
Been here thousands of times. Trails are well kept, however beware of mud after rains. Beach access is easy and close to parking. Definitely worth the Discover Pass.

Horrible atmosphere! Barking dogs everywhere, ready to attack each other. So unpleasant, especially when looking for a tranquil getaway with kids. Did not feel safe or relaxed. What a shame, bc the nature is beautiful
One of my favorite places in the world. Beautiful beach. I almost always find sand dollars and oysters. Seen bald eagles. The hiking trails make you feel like you're walking in Jurassic park!
This State Park is part of South Puget Sound. I love the bridge and hiking trails. Great place to explore  nature.

name: Billy Frank Jr. Nisqually National Wildlife Refuge
address: 100 Brown Farm Rd NE, Olympia, WA 98516, USA
reviews:
once you pay the parking fee at the kiosk, turn left and you have a choice of going on the raised walkway through the marshes, to the right at the fork. Or continue on and go left and find the gravel road way. This is good choice if you want to quickly get out to view the Puget sound.

It was such a beautiful clear day that we could see all the way to Olympic national Park and Mount Olympus in the distance.

Serios photographers were out in droves on a beautiful day, with their large camera lenses, so it really is a great place for photography.  We saw a young little green frog scoot across the roadway and it seem to be learning how to jump.  Tons of geese seemed to be returning, and we enjoyed watching them land on the water. 

All of this and we were only there for 45 minutes. We will definitely be back!  Great place to visit rain or shine if you are a nature lover for photographer.  Easy walk most of the way.  Probably not easy for wheelchairs because both the walkways and the gravel road are bumpy.

A boardwalk that extends a mile into the estuary of the Nisqually River, set aside for gorgeous, sundry wildlife...  OF COURSE it's as amazing as it sounds!!

This place is just an incredible gift, easy to navigate, and great for all walking skill levels.  If you need a place to remember the peace and beauty of nature not too far away, this will not disappoint.
Awesome walk! Great for bird watchers. A bearing pair of bald eagles flew over my party several times very closely! We had a wonderful time.

Wow, lived here 10 years and our first time stopping here. Amazing place to walk and see birds, ducks, and possibly salmon on the nisqually river. The boardwalk loop is huge, also tons of other trails to do. Can easily spend half a day here.
I love this place. It's so peaceful and has lots of great places for walking. Great place to take kids for walks. I love seeing all the different birds that live and migrate here.

name: Washington State Governor's Mansion
address: Capitol Grounds, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Nice place.
Excellent free 45 minute tour
Walls and barriers don't work do they Mr. Inslee?  Why are they so prominent around your personal residence?

You can't enter the grounds but it certainly is nice to look at.  It's set upon a hill on rolling grounds with a very nice manicured lawn. You can gain some decent vantage points if you stroll around the perimeter.
The Governor never responds to my hand written, hand delivered correspondence! SAD!

name: Decatur Woods Park
address: 1015 Decatur St SW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Good park and little trail.  The playground has the foam feeling flooring, so no worries about bark or rocks getting in the shoes!  There is a loop trail that has learning signs as well. Plenty of shade, and the bathrooms are kept clean.  Additional parking is available (except on Sundays) at the church next to the park.  Great place to just sit back and relax in the shade too.  If you are into games like PoGo or WU, this is a good spot with a gym/fort and plenty of stops/inns!
A great little play area in the middle of a beautiful setting. Has a small trail that loops around with activity cards for you and the kids.

Nice little park has a track through the nearby forest and access to nearby apartments. The park has padded flooring which is nice and a restroom onsite that is well managed. There is even a basketball court nearby.
Nice little park. Dogs love it.
Very nice and fun to bring the kids and pups. Was a great place to do parties and also have some hiking trails too.

name: Woodruff Park
address: 1500 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: My 5 almost 6yo loves this place sooooo much.

Cute park. Lots of shady areas to sit. Make sure to bring a chair or a blanket because the few benches get taken up fast. Would have been nice if they made the splash area a bit bigger. That being the first splash park in Olympia, it gets busy fast. Also parking kind of sucks a bit...but mostly due to the lack of it. All in all a nice place to cool down.

My granddaughter absolutely loved it! A bunch of different water features. Some even being controlled by the kids. So many kids with huge smiles, laughing, and all ages playing together. Safe, clean, a perfect family park. A great find!
Good place to take kids
Awesome Park, I'm glad West Olympia is doing more for families!

name: Thomas W. Huntamer Park
address: 618 Woodland Square Loop SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: It's a nice park, in a "small" business park. I'm happy Lacey puts effort into decorating it for the holidays.

This is a small Park and grassy pavilion. The pavilions kind of nice. It's a place for skateboarders to hang out. It has sidewalks that just don't seem to go anywhere they just seem to wrap circles. One very odd things that they I've put picnic tables up effectively as barriers across the sidewalks.I'm not sure what the logic is for that but it does not seem to make much sense. It seems neither welcoming nor inviting.
It's usually quiet. They know how to party in Lacey & this park a great spot for that! Beautiful Christmas lights & if you're a geocacher there's a nice hide here👍. Plenty of summer time events too.
Nice quiet place to have a picnic with the family. No toys for children however.
Love this park!  The lights look amazing right now!

name: Kayak Nisqually
address: 4949 D Milluhr Rd NE, Lacey, WA 98516, USA
reviews: This was my second trip with Kayak Nisqually and did the biolum tour.  It, again, was absolutely amazing and fun.  Sam has extensive knowledge of the area, history, cultures and eras, not to mention the science and ecology of what we were experiencing.   We were provided were equipped with safety info, lots of how-to and suggestions to make our time more enjoyable.  You don't have to go far to experience serenity and beauty - it's all right here.

We had a fantastic tour with Kayak Nisqually.  So glad to see something available in the south sound.  Sam has a great aptitude for instruction and safety for all skill levels.  He is also very knowledgeable about the local environment and history.  It was an awesome trip.

Sam was amazing with our various aged, various ability group.  We had a full group of 10 and we all came together after reading the novel The Highest Tide by Jim Lynch which was set in the Nisqually Delta.  Sam tailored his marine biology knowledge (and his knowledge of the novel) to our group.  We loved it and highly recommend kayaking with Sam!
Had an amazing bio-luminescence tour with Sam. He’s very knowledgeable and passionate about the ecosystem. Bonus: got to paddle next to very curious seals 👌🏻Would highly recommend.

Great experience with a personal touch very much above and beyond the typical “canned” tour. We got a lot of very cool information about the local ecology and history. Our guide took his time to get us up close to the wildlife; we saw lots of baby seals, eagles, and other cool birds. Our group had people of all different skill levels and our guide did a great job of accommodating everyone and making sure everyone had fun. Would definitely do a tour with them again.

name: Nisqually Reach Nature Center
address: 4949 D Milluhr Rd NE, Olympia, WA 98516, USA
reviews: A nice short walk from a nearby neighborhood. Lots of parking available. Discover pass needed. I saw a heron fishing for breakfast & this bald eagle swooped by me & landed in a near by tree to survey the scene. There’s also a boat launch ramp. I just may have to put my kayak in & check out the wildlife... when it’s a warmer.
Wish there wasn't trash, maybe more life.

Fabulous location.  Marvelous and knowledgable staff, including the amazing Director!  Great summer classes for students.  All around, tremendous contributions to the Nisqually Reach area.  Thanks for all you have done and are doing!

This is a wonderful treasure that most folks may not know about.  A great place to learn about the amazing ecosystem we have in our back yards with the nisqually  delta.  Bring the kids.  Fun and interesting for the whole family.

I love this place.  Dan is an enthusiastic educator. I hope a gift comes along soon to modernize this facility - it's an excellent place to learn about our Sound. Bring boots and plan your trip for low tide if you want the full experience.

name: Millersylvania State Park
address: 12245 Tilley Rd SW, Olympia, WA 98512, USA
reviews: Best camping place ever. Tent spots, trailer/RV spots, yurts, a cottage for rent, two swimming holes, concessions stand, kayak rentals, fishing dock, boat launch, trails for biking and walking, everything you want. Cell service is spotty but has improved these past few years. But that’s good because camping isn’t about being on your phone, it’s about being in nature and with the people you love. Our family has been coming here every single year for almost 40 years now. It’s known as Deep Lake to us because my grandparents started going to the Deep Lake Resort next door. Rangers are friendly and helpful. Reservations available online, book early because they fill up quick! They have showers and bathrooms accessible in multiple different spots around the grounds. They also have picnic tables and kitchens near the beaches. I just love this place with my whole heart.

Rented the Environmental Learning Center for a group event...fantastic facilities and great support from the rangers and staff. Best equipped kitchen we've used at any park or other event space - top-notch with walk-in cooler, convection ovens, and Hobart dishwasher. Made our food prep and serving a breeze! The cabins are tiny but toasty warm, and the showers are totally reasonable for a camp. Highly recommended for large-ish (75-80 person) groups.
Always a wonderful time at millersylvania State Park. Kids love and we love the peace and quiet. It happened to snow today which made the park look so cool.
It was cool! In the summer I'm sure it's even better! Got my kids and their cousins pic done here and they turned out great!
Great hiking trails. Be prepared for muddy spots if you go early in the year. Very beautiful.

name: Overlook Point Park
address: 1205 Barnes Blvd SW, Tumwater, WA 98512, USA
reviews: Great view of Rainier. Killer!! The overlook is in a housing development in Tumwater Falls, which was not at all what I expected, but beautiful and kind of quirky.
Very nice place to get a bird's eye view!
Beautiful views

Fantastic views of Olympia and the mountain! I only gave it four instead of five stars because it's tiny and you really can't do any walking around. It's meant for people to come and enjoy the view, which is totally worth it!
Great views on clear days.

name: Burfoot Park
address: 6927 Boston Harbor Rd NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: Its beautiful on a summer day! Theres a great little hikeing trail to get there. The waters really clear and calm, my kids loved it! We found shells and cool rocks. Just a really great place

Nice beach area with lots of little creatures to find under the rocks! Be sure to check the tides before visiting. Perfect location for large picnic parties with friends. There’s bathrooms located at the beginning of the trailhead. Play area for the kids, and many gazebos for parties.
Just jumped in the water in feburary. It was cold. Found a cool rock shrine. It was cool. Very pretty place 10/10.

Beautiful park! Plenty of space for throwing a frisbee around as well as great nature trails with informative signs and beach access! Well maintained. Trails to the beach can be a bit steep so keep that in mind.

Absolutely love this place! They have lots of picnic and barbecue areas, playground is little small but the massive amounts of green grass areas make up for it. The trails down to the beach are very nice and my toddlers & tots do great on them with a hand or two! It's like jungle they say! Even nice to go when it's raining because the trees on the trails keep you covered for the most part.

name: Nisqually Red Wind Casino
address: 12819 Yelm Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA
reviews: One can almost always expect to be greeted with a genuine friendly welcoming by the front door security department. They have a very large non-smoking area with a variety of slot games and a few table games.  In one of their bars they offer live music, food, and a great atmosphere. They have several non-alcoholic beverage stations that are above that expected when it comes to free! Their Players Club has combined with their cashier so you don't have to wait until lines to do different types of transactions. Most of the employees are very friendly which is hard to come by nowadays.

This place is always great. It holds a special place as my dad worked there for 10 years he is too sick for anything now but some of my best adult memories of him where from there. Dressed in a suit he was head of security . So when I go it reminds me of him when he was well and that alone is worth going. However I also love to game there all my favorite slots are under that roof! Including copper dropper , stinking rich and the money machine ! Yet to hit any jackpot but I still enjoy the atmosphere it gets very busy and although it's goood for business its less fun for the player looking to okay their favorite machine .

The casino itself is nice enough and the non-smoking area is one of the better in the state but the issue is rewards for loyal customers.  The Red Wind changed the way they give out rewards to loyal customers.  I have talked to numerous patrons and all have received significant reductions to nearly a third of what was previously received.  In the future I will drive to the Lucky Eagle which gives a much better reward and has a nice non-smoking area.

Went for the Drawing every 1/2 on a Thursday. Ate at the Seafood and Steak House. My wife ordered Small House Salad with Huckleberry dressing and Crab Cakes. I ordered Chicken and Mushrooms Fettuccini. It came with soup or salad, l had Clam Chowder 👌. The complimentary bread is soft and tasty with whipped butter. We were given a tiny scoop of sorbet to cleanse the pallet 👍. Plenty of covered parking for the rainy season. We used our players Rewards card to pay for Dinner, too Cool. The slots let me play for a little bit 🤑

Went here from a recommendation and was pleasantly surprised.  Plenty of newer games. Good table action.  The buffet was above average.  And the bar band Stir Crazy was one of the best cover bands I've seen.  Overall a great experience.

name: Capitol State Forest
address: Olympia, WA 98512, USA
reviews: Great place to explore the outdoors. Ive seen lots of deer here. Ive been here a lot also. You will need a Discover pass. The road system is very good. You can drive for days. Google maps works very well here. Use it. It is easy to get turned around. Fill up the tank before you go.
Lots of beautiful views once you get up high. We love cruising in our public lands

I'm up there on Rock Candy Mountain all the time driving around and I kind of like it up there it's interesting and I learned things about the roads that they have up there so I'm going to give it all these stars all five of them that's what I think of it and thank you for letting me say something
One of my favorite places to ride and hike. Camping at Middle Waddle Creek makes it so convenient.
One of my most favorite places to ride quads, hunt and just enjoy the outdoors. Always clean too.

name: Barclift Park
address: 690 Barclift Ln SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: This park is really nice. It has a tennis court, a shaded place for a picnic, and the playground was in great shape. We walked, but there's a couple of parking spaces near by too. We went in the morning in late July so it was a bit too hot to play on for an extended period of time. Although, the trees look like they'd provide shade in the late afternoon.
Nice neighborhood park with some unique toys. Kids really enjoyed it here. Also had a nice paved walk for walking, bikes, scooters. Paved path does have hills.
Great park. Tumwater takes such good care of their parks.

Nice quiet neighborhood park great for a dog walk. Only downside is no public restroom. Very pretty and relaxing some fun little paths through a small wooded area up by the neighborhood entrance. Love it here!
Epic place to hang out with friends after going to 7/11

name: Monarch Sculpture Park and Art Center
address: 8431 Waldrick Rd SE, Tenino, WA 98589, USA
reviews: What a surprising delight! Had no idea this was so close to home, been sharing it with all of my friends, coworkers and customers. It's a wonderful place filled with a lot of emotion (if you're with an artist mindset). It's incredible, everyone has asked me where these photos are from and what the story is behind it. I'd love more details for each piece to understand the perception of the artist but I have no problem coming up with my own. Love this place and will definitely come back!
Was free and very interesting sculptures. Think I missed some of the park, but was there for a couple hours looking around. Was awesome random find. Definitely a diamond in the rough!

Great stop along the Western Chehalis trail. Parking for bikes or cars, porta potty and complimentary water. Nice walking trail through the park but could be difficult for strollers, walkers or wheelchairs as the trails are not paved and there are areas with incline. Great place for a picnic, they have picnic tables scattered throughout. The scenery and setting in the natural environment is just as beautiful as any of the sculptures.  The butterfly maze was not open as of memorial day 2019, but should be in July.  It is free to visit, but you should leave a donation to support this wonderful park.

One of the coolest places I've been in Washington, it is way larger than I thought it was going to be! All of the art and sculptures are amazing, definitely worth checking out! I'll be back soon without a doubt
What a cool place. Thank you so much for your passion and openness. The world is a better place for having this place.

name: Medicine Creek Winery
address: 947 Old Pacific Hwy SE, Olympia, WA 98513, USA
reviews: when you step into this place, you'll fall in love in a heart beat. trust me on that
Currently closed due to illness. Make sure to look at their calendar before attempting to go.

Really amazing place.  Eclectic decor and fun staff.  Wine was surprisingly good.  Nothing like it within 75 miles.  Check it out.  Try a slushy wine.  Normally I would be highly against such a thing as a wine purist but it's refreshing and a fun drink for summer.

What a lovely place! Sit in a beautiful rose garden on a comfy couch with your wine samples! Wow! You won't regret stopping here for a taste of their tasty wines. I especially liked their Stagecoach mix ( a robust red) Look at the pix, their bar and bar back are exquisite wooden pieces brought from England, it's worth stopping just to see the place even if you don't drink wine! And the proprietor is a delight as well, genuinely friendly, she loves what she does and it shows.

About a month ago three of us paid a visit to this wonderful winery, this my second visit. They only make red wines which I appreciate because a small winery can't, in my opinion, produce fantastic wines if they try to make too many varietals. The ambiance is quite unique with a very friendly staff, contributing to an extremely enjoyable visit.

name: Mima Mounds Natural Area Preserve
address: 12315 Waddell Creek Rd SW, Olympia, WA 98512, USA
reviews: I expected very little but with my 3.5 year old this hike/ walk is PERFECT. We brought his balance bike, and it is flat enough that I don't have to worry, but still has lots of small dips here and there for him to go downhill and practice risk taking. I kind of like that there are no trees because I can see everything, who's coming down the trail, animals, etc. It feels very safe for this mom of 2 hiking without Dad around.
It's a nice place to take a walk and relax.  The mounds are pretty interesting to see, but it's not one of the places I go out of my way to visit.
Loved this place but can't wait to go here in the spring and summer time. We went during the fall.
Great place to visit with kids! Easy to get around with a nice paved pathway.

Pretty neat geographic phenomenon.  The kids enjoyed debating what caused mound formation.  Not much to see other than the mounds but something all Washingtonians should see.  Must have a state park pass and be prepared for noise from a near by gun range.

name: Old Capitol Building
address: 600 Washington St SE, Olympia, WA 98504, USA
reviews: An extremely beautiful historic old capitol building. Great architecture and stained glass. Nice park in front of it. Unfortunately there are a lot of homeless people sleeping in the park in front of it now. It is still worth seeing.

This place is so beautiful! Very peaceful, would definitely recommend to go visit this place with family or friends. Inside it’s amazing all of the hard work that was put into building this place is amazing. The town it’s safe is very small and quit. But definitely recommend to stop by and check it out if your driving by you won’t regret it! To park I believe it was $10 but to enter in we didn’t have to pay anything.  Also if your into photography it’s a great place to get some amazing pictures in.
Beautiful building, I wish I could see it from inside. the type of people on the street around are not the type you want to meet.

Visitors are allowed thirty minutes at this historical building. Well worth viewing some original features: 1. Original marble restrooms; 2. Fourth floor stained glass, surrounded by uncovered brick and stone materials; 3. First floor documents' vault (now an office); 4. Intricate architectural details throughout their multiple floors.
this is the first time i see such a unique building.

name: Regional Athletic Complex
address: Olympia, WA 98513, USA
reviews: This is a very clean and accessible sports complex. Handicap parking is available,  concession stand, and bathrooms with working toilets. We were very pleased with this area. Only down side is its next to a mushroom farm so occasionally it stinks
It was beautiful and clean. Easily accessible n fun.

More than enough parking for softball tournament. Great playground for all ages. The fields we're turf in place of dirt. Tons of caged stadium seating. Lots of low maintenance restrooms. Snack shack sells kettle corn. Overall well maintained park!
Lots of parking and good soccer fields. Dress appropriately and bring sunglasses! The wind whips across the fields pretty good.

Great place to hang out with the kids...plenty of open space, handy dog waste receptacles all over, lots of shady places to hang out, walking trails and pathways, lots of bathrooms and parking, shelters (with grills and electrical outlets) that can be reserved for special occasions, and SO much more!!! It's worth the visit on any day of the week!

name: Frye Cove County Park
address: 4000 61st Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: One of the best parks with access to the water in the local Olympia/Shelton area. Play equipment, shelters, toilets and grills.
Hills/trails are kind of high and dark in the woods, but great experience. Great exercise!
Grew up coming to this Park and it remains one of the most beautiful places I've been.

Very nice place to relax, cool salt water experience, even saw a seal up close. Bath house was a bit old school. The one complaint I had was advertisment/signs or direction are no were to be found. The only reason I stopped was because I was looking for a place to fish which is very hard to do because everything on the water is private. Good for the rich lol....just not for me.
Beautiful trails. Well maintained park. Family friendly.

name: Sandstone Distillery
address: 842 Wright Rd SE, Tenino, WA 98589, USA
reviews:
We had a great time at Sandstone! Everyone was knowledgeable about their products and very friendly. We got to try a great variety of liquors (one vodka, two gins, three whiskeys and a bourbon). I liked that they also carry a locally made tonic syrup and sipping vinegars (these were fascinating to try!). I also enjoyed how everything had a story and they weren't shy about telling those stories. Especially enjoyable: all of the ingredients are locally sourced, their processes are all very environmentally friendly, and even the spent grains have a useful home.

I'd highly recommend this if you have a couple of hours to spare; get the tour, try some tasty booze, support a local business! Win/win for everyone.

Awesome little small batch distillery! Stopped by since it was close to a wedding venue. Great little tour and delicious sampling flight. I actually liked their gin which surprised me. They also had a delicious coffee liqueur. Plenty of potential!

We had an awesome experience as ‘Distillers for the Day’ with John, Justin and Randy st Sandstone. From grain to gulp, we were hands on in every step of the process working alongside the distillers and truly emerging ourselves in the science and sweat equity of craft distilling. It was fun, interesting, active and we had a lot of laughs along the way. I highly recommend Sandstone. Heart and hustle goes into everything they produce with a true local, sustainable and artisan theme throughout every drop of the final bounty!  The bacon whiskey is to die for!
Great way to spend a Thursday afternoon! Thanks, John for the tour and tasting. Excellent product..awards are well deserved :0)   Kathy & Linda

AWESOME distillery!! Great whiskey, great gin, great people! My husband and I were welcomed right in for a tour & tastings! Dont leave without trying their signature vinegars! Mind blowing stuff over here.

name: Lake Lois Habitat Reserve
address: Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: The trails are not in great shape with several blockages. Overall it was a nice walk, not strenuous at all. If you were running the trail, you might need to be careful not to twist your ankle on the narrow unkempt paths.
Lots of fun. Quiet place. No toys.
Great little habitat reserve. Only downfall is there are a couple tents pitched throughout which already weirds me out.
Small area kept up by the Boy Scouts. Nice and clean, just somewhat small. Excellent for young children and elderly
Not too many people. For beautiful over the water.

name: Exit Puzzles Escape Room
address: 109 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Did this with a few friends for my birthday. Had a fantastic time. This was challenging, but solvable. This was my first escape room, but I'll be back to do their other room soon. 

I cannot stress this enough, YOU SHOULD CHOOSE THIS ESTABLISHMENT if you are interested in escape rooms. Others in my group had been to other rooms, and this was by, BY FAR, their favorite. 

And our guide, Kyle, was awesome. I'd give this 7 stars if that were an option.
We did the new puzzle, Museum of Curiosity, for a work team building activity. Lots of fun! We had done The Landlord previously and this one was even better. Highly recommend!

I had so much fun! Highly recommend that you get a group of friends/family on this adventure. Communication is key and the puzzles are fun! Great for a team building exercise or even birthday outing. No adventure is quite the same. Probably the best escape room in the PNW!

Amazing rooms! The second room, while much harder than their first one, is really well done with a lot of puzzles that everyone can work on - nobody is sitting around (u less they want to... I guess?)!
Top quality puzzles.  Are you an expert?  Ask for the expert version.  You won't be sorry.  11 out of 10, would definitely go again.

name: Long Lake Park
address: 2790 Carpenter Rd SE, Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews: This is a great place has free life vests, kayak rentals for a few, and life guards most of the time. But can fill up fast because it is small. Big trun around for large vehicles

The dock is gone but the lake seems more family friendly now that the police have started having more of a presence here.  Last year there were far more people smoking weed and sneaking alcohol around the park.  From what I saw during our recent visit it was much improved.

4 stars because the bathrooms reek like a porta-potty.
Beautiful, safe and fun. There are bathrooms, concessions, police on duty and a lifeguard. Only bummer is there's no dock or anything for the kids to jump off of.
Usually a lot of people when it's nice out but a pretty clean park nice dock on the water front clean bathrooms and nice green grass to sit on in the sun!

First time here. The water is so clean and the view is absolutely stunning. There is a lot of parking and it's free. There is a very large area of lush green grass to throw a towel or picnic blanket down. I like that the water is divided into shallow and deep and the dock is a nice feature for the older kids. Minus one star because there is no sand here, just rocks.

name: Hope Island Marine State Park
address: Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Wonderful state park, really fun to paddle out to it. The apple orchard and the deer make it even more fun. I can't wait to bring my whole family out there.

Really nice park, lots of trails and beaches between high tides. Accessible only by boat. Boat masters beware of unmarked large underwater rock at lower tides on the SW corner. Keep your eyes on the depth finder
Amazing park. Quiet.  No electricity, no roads, no running water. Great place to canoe hike around the island and just relax. Pack it in pack it out and enjoy.

A home away from home. Definitely worth seeing the sunset from the island on a clear day.  A great chance to paddle alongside with seals. If you go through in the correct season you can even see whales.

Puget Sound paradise. Hope Island State Park is exclusively open for canoers and kayakers to camp on. My kids and I make it out here in the canoe every year. It's an adventure worth repeating year after year. The thrill of exploring the Sound in a canoe and then exploring the island doesn't get old. This is the preserved beauty of the Puget Sound.

name: Sequalitchew Creek Trail Head
address: Sequalitchew Creek Trail, DuPont, WA 98327, USA
reviews:
Great easy trail going in and out. Can be a bit muddy, especially after rain, so be sure to bring your rough shoes.
This trail isn't a loop trail, but rather a hike-in hike-out-the-way-you-came type trail. Once you get to the end however it's great. Great history and a great view of the Puget Sound. Be sure though to stay off the big tracks at the end of the trail that run over the tunnel. These are very very active rails and high speed passenger trains use these tracks so be careful.

Nice walk, maybe takes 20 minutes, perfect length for an afternoon picnic. Love all the train stuff and seeing the trains come by. Nice Pebble Beach to enjoy. Not much shade to be found at the beach. Nice little girl scape not to far from Lakewood, will be my new go to picnic spot.

Short, wide, well worn, partially paved 1.5 mile trail through an evergreen forest, skirting a small creek and ending at the sound. Its fairly busy, you can expect to run into at least 5 or 6 other groups, possibly with on or off leash dogs. Occasionally requires a skip hop over muddy patches. Mostly level, but generally felt like it has a slow decline going out, and the obvious reciprocal incline going back. Good for a 1 to 5 mile run.

Good 3 mile round trip out and back. Pet friendly. Partially paved but mostly unpaved. We did ok with a big tire stroller. The water views are amazing once you get to the end. Minus one star for no clearly accessible public restrooms we could see.

Nice shorter hike, 1.5 miles to the water, just under the bridge, 3 mile round trip total. The path is part hard ball and part gravel but in good condition. The view at the end point is spectacular, and there is plenty of space along the beach there to walk, salvage, or just hang out. City Hall and the police/fire station is at the trail head if you need to use the bathroom or have an emergency. There is plenty of space to park in the field across the street if the lot ends up being full. Overall nice little hike and getting to learn a bit of local history via the signage they put up is a bonus

name: Horizon Pointe Park
address: 5700 Ruddell Rd SE, Lacey, WA 98513, USA
reviews: The park is conveniently located and accessible to the  neighbor community. There's plenty of grass for all kinds of activities.
Small neighbor park with playground and covered picnic area and large grass field. Very pretty.
Big grass area to run around!
It was fun my boys played scorer
Stopped by to check out the national night out thing. Seems kinda fun, lots of small vendors and smells like good food cooking. Will be stopping by again with the family

name: La Petite Maison
address: 101 Division St NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: This is one of the best hidden gems on the west coast. It’s literally a husband and wife. The service is amazing, wine list is great, and most of all the food is always great. Get the 5-course meal about $60/person and it will not disappoint. They are very accommodating. It’s fine dining without being pretentious. LOVE THIS PLACE!!

Superb gourmet menu cooked and served perfectly. Chef/owners & servers are AMAZING—they go beyond expectations to make your dining experience exceptional. Go here for special occasions or for a wonderful glass of wine and appetizers. Cater your next special occasion with delicious selection.

Had dinner here with my girlfriends. Everyone was astonished by the meal. It’s been years since I’ve been in, since I don’t live in the area. Absurd. This little gem is one of the best dining experiences in the world, and it’s in little Olympia. The wines by the glass were all beautiful, and we had many.  The service was incredible. I had a filet that was cooked to perfection. Every detail is executed to the fullest potential of the dish. Go here if you know food.
Fantastic from the service to the food to the ambiance. Not a single complaint. Fantastic place for a date night.
We always have an amazing experience. The dishes are delicious and service is with a smile. Thank you and we can hardly wait to be back!

name: Cascadia Grill
address: 200 4th Ave W, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Very friendly staff and atmosphere.    Amazing food.   One of my favorite places to eat downtown Olympia.  Great job guys.    Keep it up.  We'll see you again soon.   :)))

Friendly and welcoming environment! the outdoors theme was very fun to look at. The food was absolutely delicious! I enjoyed the southern fried chicken sandwich! And the fries are some of the best I've ever had! Definitely cannot wait to return!

Fantastic service and amazing food. Went on a Tuesday night for a celebration and it was calm with delightful music. The best cheesecake I have tasted in my entire life! If you get anything here get the white chocolate raspberry cheesecake! The only thing I'd change is offering an entire cake of it! Perfect first introduction to this place.

Amazing amazing! A vegan/vegetarian menu and regular menu. So much to choose from. I had the bomb creole fried chicken sandwich and the wife had the vegan version. The chilli cheese fries were sweet. Had vegan carrot cake to top it off. Will come back again

I absolutely love this place, the vibes, the people, the menu, the music, the decor. Just a fantastic restaurant with great, personable service, good options of craft beer and delicious food, amazing desserts, affordable, and more. Conveniently located too! Highly recommend to all living in Oly or even to those passing through.

name: Dockside Bistro & Wine Bar
address: 501 Columbia St NW Suite B, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: High Quality Takeout. During the virus restaurant shutdown order, I wanted to have a special dinner with my sweetie but was stymied until I heard Dockside Bistro was doing takeout, and what great takeout it is! I went to the website, looked at the menu and called in an order. The person who took the order was friendly and helpful. When I picked it up I was glad to see I could get it at the window on the boardwalk so did not need to go in. Laurie  greeted us pleasantly. I've been there before and felt good knowing the place is always super clean, and now it's even cleaner. As she brought out the order she cleaned her hands with bleach wipes and even had a clean pen to sign with, which then went in the used pens glass!
