The food was tasty, healthy, and beautifully presented, not your average takeout. (The fish tacos are awesome.) It wasn't cheap, but it was worth it. We took it home and had our special dinner on the patio. The only downside is that it took her longer than I expected to assemble the food and put together the bill, but, again, it was worth it.

Slightly under seasoned... the duck and the stone crab soup were under seasoned and therefore underwhelming. 

Halibut was excellent.  

Overall the meal was good, but not great. Certainly not the 5 star ravings you see on here.
Best food I've ever had in my life. Those tea smoked scallops made me cry. Romantic but comfortable, excellent lighting, thoughtful service. I see you Olympia! We will be back.

Picked-up items from their special menu (during pandemic/social distancing closure) and enjoyed some outstanding Dungeness Crab Chowder, Goat Cheese Salad & Lemongrass Chicken Skewers. While a wee bit pricey, you'd be hard pressed to find "take out" of this caliber anywhere else in town. YUM!!
Very nice restaurant with a view of the harbor. Had the Elk which was very good. Parking was easy for the time we were there.

name: Basilico Ristorante
address: 507 Capitol Way S, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Little Italy in Olympia! Such a gem in food quality and presentation. Staff went above and beyond to accommodate our large party.  Large gluten-free selection and gluten-free bread for appetizers. Delicious pasta with vegetarian and vegan options available. Highly recommend.
Authentic Italian food and lot of vegetarian and vegan options. Great selection of wine too.
Celebrated our 1 year anniversary dinner at Basilico. Alexis was our server, she was awesome and the food and drinks were suburb.  Will definitely return and try other menu options.

I can't recommend this place highly enough. I have eaten there twice and I have no idea why it hasn't been a lot more. The staff was very friendly. The food was amazing, the tomato bisque was probably the tastiest soup I have ever had. The meals we had were all very delicious and for dessert we had a chocolate mousse that I will be dreaming about for weeks.

We have been to Basilico half a dozen times or more and each time it's been an amazing experience. This time we did the Discover Basilico 4 course experience. We had a full meal for leftovers tomorrow and the food was amazing! It gave us an opportunity to try 3 appetizers, 3 pastas, 2 entrees and 3 desserts. The entire experience was so amazing and the food was fabulous!! My husband ordered his favorite and he wasn't disappointed! This is the best Italian restaurant I'm WA state. My husband is Italian and he loves this place.

name: Budd Bay Cafe
address: 525 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
One can see why this place is highly regarded by the locals. Hospitality is above all among the best. From hostess to server. . . the attention to our meal' s enjoyment was obviously important. Relaxing marina view ⛵ in the twilight hour along with good mix of music 🎶 genre playing in the background made for an enjoyable meal. 
          Costs are as expected of a marina location $$$ although not upscale since linen was napkin only no t-cloth. Bread/rolls was actually a part of the meal no extra charge ... wow that's old school classy. Food flavors were acceptable but nothing that stands out as different or original. However, each plate and appetizer ordered was served hot rather than just warm... meaning wait staff was on point. Lots of cheery folks warranting a return visit.

We went to celebrate my fiance's birthday.  We had one of the best nights we've had in quite a while.  Everything from the appetizers to dessert was amazing.  We started during happy hour and the prices were very fair.  The food came out very fast and our server Trina was amazing

I was in the area and i happen to google king crab eating. 
Well, this restaurant popped up, and after an hr or two spent on just  online researching and reading reviews overall on restaurants , seafood restaurant.
I decide to go with this one. Very good food. Half a pound of king crab,  wanted to try the Dungeness crab .  They only had it served with salad. Or like a cocktail . Very good clam chowder and delicious oysters shots.
All and all, pretty good.

But now I'm going to the red wing casino for their buffet!

FABULOUS dinner and awesome wait staff, Julia. A real sweetheart. Very thoughtful and caring. I was celebrating my birthday with a friend but I was pretty uncomfortable after a medical procedure earlier in the afternoon. She even brought me ice in a bag to alleviate some pain. Thank you.

This place was so good we ate here back to back. ONE thing to note. SKIP The “jumbo shrimp cocktail” for $10 - they are not jumbo at all. Your better off ordering the shrimp scampi, as it’s like $16, you get way more food and the shrimp were the same size if not bigger. 
So delicious. The blackened salmon was amazing. Loaded baked potato. Yum!  Bread to start. Friendly service. Great dinner.

name: Gardner's Seafood & Pasta
address: 111 Thurston Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Thank you for such a wonderful experience. Food- phenomenal. Service- wow you ladies are amazing! We found the perfect bottle of wine on the wine rack up front so I recommend checking if you are a wine person :) Perfect lighting. Perfect music. Perfect.... Everything. I reserved a month in advance for Valentine's day and all that was available was 8pm. Regardless of what was surely a long night for everyone we were treated like the first customers of the night. Seating was right on time. We didn't feel rushed at all and we enjoyed a truly exceptional dinner. Kudos, Gardner's, you clearly have this figured out!

Great ambiance,food and service.  Very romantic but comfortable atmosphere. We went for our anniversary dinner and they sent a candle with the dessert we ordered along with a card signed by the staff💗

Fantastic meal! 
 We haven't been here for a number of years so we decided to give them a shot... great choice! The ambience was lovely, the service was attentive but not overbearing and the food was terrific! We had the charcuterie appetizer which was a lovely mix of meat, cheese, fruit and veggies served with soft, warm pita triangles just slightly browned. Plentiful but not so much that it spoiled our appetite for our entrees. 
 My wife had the pasta special, ravioli with Italian sausage and a ricotta/ goat cheese filling in a nice light but bright tomato sauce,  delightful. I had the scallop special and it was wonderful, four plump, perfectly prepared jumbo scallops served over a sweet potato puree that was really well done.  Dessert was a shared (huge) piece of dark chocolate layer cake with cream cheese frosting..yum!
 Thanks for seating us after a short wait without a reservation, we were lucky they were quite busy. I strongly recommend calling ahead and ensuring your spot here!

Great staff, service, and food. Never disappoints. Made me sorry that I ruined my palate with a cocktail before dinner (rough week). Felt much better after a great evening with wonderful food and a relaxed atmosphere.
We had an amazing Anniversary dinner here. Excellent service, exceptional food, lovely atmosphere. Recommend highly!

name: Anthony's Homeport Olympia
address: 704 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: We brought our small school group and got treated to a great window table with a view of the Capitol dome. Our server Jose was professional, efficient and warm. The bread was delicious. We ate from the 3 for $25 menu and were pleasantly surprised by flavor and portion size. My students loved the lemonade. The calamari was a hit. The smoked.salmon dip comes with apple slices and was recommended. Ahi nachos were delightful. The Caesar salad was crisp and refreshing. I had a med rare sirloin and it melted in my mouth. Will definitely be back again.

Delicious food, delightful drinks and a great waitress equals a wonderful night out! The roasted pear drink was fantastic and the Bailey's mousse was very tasty as well. You can't go wrong at Anthony's!
Beautiful location, nice ambience and staff but those cannot make up of the lack of flavors in food. Everything we ordered was bland. Pan fried oysters, seafood fettuccini, steak.

I couldn't believe how perfect it all was! The mellow water view, the literally PERFECT service, and the just-as-perfect food made it one of my best dining experiences in years! We traded bites and - except for the vegetarian not tasting the hamburger - had to just share it all, because we all wanted everything. I can't say enough about how amazing it was! It's not cheap - we spent $40 apiece - but we had an experience of perfection we'll remember for years...

The complimentary bread was great.
The Wasabi sauce on the ahi nacho was delicious
The four course steak was charred on the outside with little to no flavor
The award winning clam chowder wasn't flavourful, it makes me wonder what year was the award given? 
Service was mediocre, after the entree, the server didn't come to ask about our choice of dessert
The floor was wet with no "wet floor" sign

name: Pizzeria La Gitana - Olympia
address: 518 Capitol Way S, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Excellent service, the owner is so kind and generous. We can’t wait to go back for the live music and delicious food! My pizza tasted like it did when we visited Italy. You can over indulge in this pizza without getting a stomach ache because of the natural ingredients. My new favorite restaurant!

Our family of 3 enjoyed the food and atmosphere.  The service was a little off as we had to flag down servers for water, refills, and a kid color sheet that was mentioned/promised to our kiddo.  Pizza was our very quickly once we were able to place our order.  It was tasty and crust was thin (if that’s you’re preference).  We had a kid-friendly pepperoni and ham but there were lots of other fun options on the menu. Price was reasonable.  Atmosphere was very nice.  Street parking, only.

My favorite place in Olympia, Tumwater, Lacey area. The staff is welcoming, friendly, and helpful. The pizza is fresh, hot, and delicious. The wine is poured generously and the ambiance is set effortlessly.  The owner and employees have successfully brought a piece of Italy to the streets of Olympia, WA. This is my home away from home.

We went here for Valentines dinner.  We have been here a few times before and our visits have always been 4-5 stars.  They make delicious pizzas, salads, and pastas using organic food. They also offer many things that are not very common, like organic mushrooms, truffle oil, and delicious blue cheese.  This time we had a very nice antipasto board.  As usual, the management or owner is present and conversing with the customers. One negative, is their price seems to be rising rather quickly.  I realize their food is of a very fine quality, but their prices are what we would consider to be high for the area.  For the two of us, which included two wine glasses, a half antipasto board, two main pasta dishes, and a take out dish... Was almost $120.  This is high quality food, but I hope La Gitana doesnt price themselves out of business.

I have missed Italian pizza since I was in Italy. Eating here is the closest I can get and it is incredible! The staff are friendly, the owners are great and the food delicious. I love their pizzas, the salad and just tried their pasta which was equally impressive. The environment is lovely and on some days they have live music which just adds to the overall feel!

name: Iron Rabbit Restaurant & Bar
address: 2103 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Amazing food and wonderful service! The food was all top notch and generous portions! We all had something different so we could try more things and it was all fantastic. And try, if you can, to save room for the bread pudding!

Two words delicious and accommodating. We have serious allergies in my family so finding restaurants can be difficult. So after reading a few good yelp reviews we decided to cross our Fingers and see what the Iron Rabbit had to offer. Right off the bat we were able to talk to the manager about allergies and it all worked out. Everything was handled with care and the results were delicious. My two recommendations are the drunken sailor and the chicken cordon who. Not only was the food great but also the building was nice too. It had a quaint hometown feel and had clean bathrooms. I would definitely recommend stopping by.

I was on my way out of town and wanted to splurge on dinner so I decided to go here since it was in my list of restaurants to visit. I figured it would be a bit pricey since they don't have prices listed on the menu on their website. 

Overall the prices weren't too bad. I got the buffalo cauliflower to start with and it was amazing!!  Spicy and sweet with delicious chunky blue cheese dressing on the side. 

For my main course I opted to get the Wagyu Top steak instead of a burger but I wish I hadn't. For $32.00 it was very disappointing. It didn't have much flavor, was really dry and also over cooked. I asked for medium, hoping for some pink, but it was more medium well to well.  

My service was good, the guy who took care of me was friendly and attentive but after he dropped off the steak he never came back to ask how it was or else I would have told him it was too dry and over cooked. In the end I just checked it up to being part of the adventure of exploring new restaurants while on vacation.  I will add that thw mashed potatoes were really good too!

I had the seafood linguine & my wife had the drunken sailor.  Both excellent meals.  Why the 3 stars?  The deserts were horrible.  I had the bread pudding.  The back side had a burnt taste & the rest was too stiff & not "pudding " at all.  My wife had the chocolate raspberry cheesecake.  All raspberry, including seeds, with chocolate syrup spread around as garnish.  She was so disappointed.  We both had coffee & for $4.25 per, it was sad for coffee.  We'd go back for the entrees only if we were really in the mood.  Recommend skip their dessert & coffee.  Expensive mistake.

The service is very good. Very friendly staff. Good for family's or alone. They have a fantastic homemade ginger ale and root beer that was very tasty. I had the unbeatable burger and the comdoments were very tasty. The vegetarian beet burger was dry and underwhelming. My companion had the fish and chips and they said it was serviceable. I'd go back for the drinks.

name: Mediterranean Breeze
address: 2302 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Had a great experience, every item ordered was flavorful and fresh. While being served by friendly and attentive wait staff. The decor is tasteful and the seating  arrangement is comfortable and spacious. So with all these positives you do pay a price for a great eating experience, but well worth the treat to your taste buds.

This is one of the best meals I’ve ever had and I love a wide spectrum of cuisines. This is authentic Turkish cuisine made from scratch! Lezzetli!Fantastic and knowledgeable service, amazingly tasty food, imported drinks from Turkey, clean and cultured restaurant. I cannot compliment it enough. And while it may come off as pricy, the generous portions are well worth the value. Highly recommend!

My husband and I came here for the first time tonight. This restaurant is quite the treasure in Olympia. Food was absolutely delicious! Atmosphere was very pleasant and service was outstanding. I love the fact this place is family run, you can tell there is a pride in ownership by the quality of the food. Can't wait to come back and try something new!

Wow, the meal was amazing! We had no idea what to expect, from a price or quality standpoint. Fair warning- Specials can be a bit pricey ($30-$35 )for the Olympia area but entrees ran a little lower cost. 
Everything we had was delicious. I had a sampler of 3 kinds of meat and it was fantastic. There were no leftovers. My wife had a more standard dish that utilized a sauce that came with mine; Iskender something.
Decor is as expected, Turkish themed but not overbearing. The room is very spacious and the layout looked like it could accommodate larger groups as well.

Nice presentation,service was less than acceptable.  Server disappeared and we never got refills of our coffee or tea and had to ask another waiter if we could have our bill. However the food was good and the one Turkish  coffee I received and the one Turkish tea my friend received was amazing, wish we could have ordered more.

name: Waterstreet Cafe
address: 610 Water St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: It had been a long time since I'd gone to Waterstreet Cafe.  The atmosphere is very nice though on a Saturday night very loud.  If you want a quiet evening conversation during peak hours this would not be the place for you. .We chose three small plates to share, and aside from the food being delicious, I felt the portions were generous.  We also chose two of their specialty cocktails, and both were very good and well presented.  I would definitely recommend Waterstreet Cafe.  I have never been disappointed.
Brought a cousin from out of town and she adored the outdoor seating and the quality of the food.

I had a hard time finding a parking spot so from the get go it was wonky. The trees were covering their sign out front so I didn't immediately spot them. I ordered the antipasti, it was good but the calamari my friend ordered was way over salted and the waitress forgot my other friends salad. The waitress was spilling the water every time she refilled my cup and didn't bother to clean it up, she just walked away. Needless to say I was very unimpressed with my experience. There's many other restaurants within walking distance from them that have good service and incredible food.
I ate the best salmon soup I ever tried! And the sandwiches are great! Totally recommend!
Great little hidden away restaurant. Wonderful location, close to everything in downtown Olympia. With interesting varieties to choose from. Parking can be a chore though.

name: Anthony's Hearthfire Grill Olympia
address: 1675 Marine Dr NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Amazing food and matching customer service. We went in a group of 6, and were expecting more people to come. The staff was very understanding and accommodating. The other didn't turn up but we were served with utmost courtesy. They even custom made a dish for he vegetarian member of our group without any issue. Highly recommended. The setting is beautiful with great views.

Been here several times, and wanted to ackowledge the fantastic service and food being prepared by this place! The birthday dinner that I had with my friends. I had seen a menu item on line, but the menu on the table didn't have that particular item.  The manager came out and said they certainly could make the item I had requested, and I said at what price? She answered at the same price.  I was very impressed.  The meal was outstanding!  Then to top it off, she asked if I would like a complimentary desert for my celebration! I told her I was full but would love a chocolate martini!  She brought it over with a smile, and at no charge!!! This was by far the best service I have ever had in my life.  I am a senior, and wish I could give more stars.
Amazing food and drink options. Love their sunset dinners. Happy hour is always a great time. Gets busy so call in advance for your expected rush times.

Nice place right on the water (during high tide).  Lots of window seating to watch Hooded Mergansers, Buffleheads, various seagulls and...a rainbow!  I think the rainbow was a unique addition, but...it was unique!  Good food.  Went during the "lunch" menu so it was perfect for smaller eaters. I had the salmon and she had the roasted chicken (roasted on the spit) salad.  I wouldn't say the ambience is "cozy" but it's very nice and on clear days you can see the Olympic Mts.

As someone else said it's a nice place to take guests.

Even got to watch a Dragon Boat crew work out!
We really enjoyed the shrimp and steaks. The glaze on the steaks was awesome. Service and the staff was wonderful. Thank you for a very nice Valentine's Day dinner.

name: Chelsea Farms Oyster Bar
address: 222 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: What a great experience, we have been wanting to try this place for a little while now. Glad we did today, excellent service very prompt and friendly. And the oysters were so flavorful and fresh. Also a must have is the clam chowder and steamer clams.I highly recommend everyone try this place. More then just seafood as well here.

Our visit was a nice lunch. We tried the shucker special which allowed us to try a dozen oysters. The oysters were amazing each pair  was a different experience.My wife had a lavender drop which she loved so much she had two! I tried a beer called black mountain it was delicious. For our entrees we had the shrimp and grits and the Mac and cheese with added crab. The only thing we would change was the cold crab on top of the mac and cheese outside of that this place was great! The restaurant was beautiful and the staff was very attentive. We will definitely be back to try the brunch and dinner menus. Thank you for a wonderful lunch!

Came in tonight with my friend looking for some good baked oysters. Ended up being completely amazed by both the quality of the food and the incredible service! Lauren was super knowledgeable about the entire menu and extremely friendly.  All in all an incredible experience! Would definitely  recommend and will for sure be returning.

Every time I come to this restaurant, I'm filled with so much joy because I know that I'm in for an absolute treat. With the new opening of their extended restaurant area, I love sitting at the bar and watching them shuck the oysters and create beautiful plates full of yummy treats. Even my husband, who isn't huge on seafood, finds yummy things to eat here.

Delicious food and cocktails, reasonably priced - in a modern, light, sophisticated space.  We ordered every oyster on the menu (about 10 varieties listed with origin & tasting notes).  We were in shellfish heaven.  Look for their daily happy hour - called something like "Shucker's Call" for $3 oysters.
Then came their fabulous clam chowder.  This is a more modern, light take on chowder. Not too heavy on the cream with the freshest clams, pork belly and potatoes.  Soul satisfying.
The airy space has large windows, with gray & white decor, mostly spare with a touch of whimsy.
Parking is easy - there is an adjacent parking lot for the entire complex and ample street spaces.

name: Tugboat Annie's
address: 2100 W Bay Dr NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews:
Great views and delicious food!  Was recently here for a computer gaming event and had breakfasts both days!   

Country Fried Steak with Eggs and the Biscuits and Gravy.  

Good flavor 👌 Just wish they had hash browns! 😁

On the nightside of the things, I ordered an adult Almond Joy shake.   It was tasty, just wished it had a little more punch to it.  😉

Love coming here and looking forward to visiting again!

Been coming here for years with a LAN renting the downstairs and sometimes on our own. Every time the drinks, food, and service have been exemplary. Breakfast, the clam chowder, everything is awesome. You can't beat the view and you owe it to yourself to visit, especially since it's a little off the beaten path (a big plus).
Get some friends together and come to have some fun and maybe even try the Barge Burger. The biggest burger you've ever seen!

Great views.  Good food.  Humble & Casual.  Amazing location to take a little break from it all.  Attentive folks and some innovative takes on classic American fare.  Honestly, one of my wife's favorite places here in the Olympia area.

Hubby and I went to lunch at Tugboat Annie's! Was delicious! The crab and artichoke dip appetizer was yummy! I loved my shrimp and chips, and hubby  enjoyed his clam and chips basket! The service was the Best! Can't wait to go again. We will make it one of our favorite spots! I look forward to seeing what the harbor looks like at night! What a cool place!🐋🐚🐳

Great place for a meal! The food was yummy and well priced.  They have a kids meal and my son had the grilled cheese.  I had the shrimp and my husband had the pulled pork, both were great.  Server was very friendly.  Super busy at dinner time but had plenty of parking and lots of tables/seating.  They have option to sit outside as well.  Great views all around the outside of the restaurant.

name: Old School Pizzeria
address: 108 Franklin St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Old school is classic Olympia pizza eats. Buy by the slice or whole pizzas. Lots of fun decor on the walls. Sometimes nice staff sometimes a bit on the cold side, but it doesn't alter my experience. I love their pizza, they're one of the best in town.

It's the best NYC style pizza in Olympia. Real thin crust, nice stretchy cheese and a good flavor to the sauce without being overpowering. If you like the sauce a bit more punchy, you can add parmesan, oregano, and red peppers. I find it perfect, maybe just a little shy in sauce flavor. It's not burned, but it gets a good char in a few spots like you see in my pics. The atmosphere is, well, old school. They nailed it perfectly, even down to the rad old school video games. If you're in your 40's and 50's, you'll probably love the place and feel at home. I love it. The music is loud, so this isn't the joint for a business meeting or romantic evening alone.
This place is a breath of fresh air. I feel like a kid again. Endless drinks. Food is great. I had 2 slices of pepperoni. Lots of attention to detail. This place is a must visit!

My childhood all in one bite. Use to go to this place all the time growing up in Olympia. Very happy to come back 10 years later and see it still up and doing well!! Serving out the best pizza like I remember back as a kid! Try their thick slice pizzas it was so yummy. 
Just came up from Portland on my way to Seattle and we had to stop for pizza. And I think I am going to have to stop again on the back home! My fave pizza place! Love the 80's vibe its got with rock and roll posters and old writing all over the walls. Cool music playing. Great vibes all around.

I went 3 years ago when my son and his family lived there. They recommended it and I was not disappointed. Very tasty pizza and great selection of local beers. Cool and quirky place that I would definitely go back to next time I'm in the area.

name: Lemon Grass Restaurant
address: 212 4th Ave W, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Awesome food made fresh. Friendly staff. Clean bathrooms.
Excellent food and great service! Staff were very friendly and helpful! Nice atmosphere and tasty food! Prices are reasonable! I love and recommend  their Chinese Sausage Fried Rice!

Straight-up, delicious meal! Fresh vegetables, quality meats, delectable sauces! MmmMmm...

Glad we stopped here on our tour thru Olympia. 😁

Outstanding, large menu. Extensive vegetarian options. Great cooking. Great staff. Tasteful decor and atmosphere. They have different options for how spicy you want it. The portions, however, were way too large. To-go boxes were necessary for everyone and it encouraged me to eat way too much all at once. I definitely will come back to try more.
So incredibly delicious! Plus they can customize any dish, do half orders, customize your spice level etc. I ordered the Singapore noodle and it was SO good! Will definitely order it again and again.

name: Vic's Pizzeria Wildwood
address: 2822 Capitol Blvd SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Atmosphere was good. Pizza was pretty decent, not the best but pretty decent. Ordered two 18 inch pies and they came VERY slow. Customer service was not great either. They offered plates but never brought them, I had to go get them. I had to ask for a pitcher of water it was not offered and then I had to ask for ice as well. I would recommend ordering before arriving or calling for to go.
The pizza is very tasty and they have a good selection of beer and cider.  The employees are very nice and efficient.  I will definitely be returning.

Pizza tasted like pumpkin. I thought I was eating a Thanksgiving meal. Loads of cheese, big flop... Overall 4.7 out of 10. 
80% of the pie wound up in the trash

Amazing as always!
Friendliest staff and great family environment! Slices for a quick bite or full pizzas made to order... and the vegan pizza is by far the best around! 
Love this place!
Amazing pizza & beer (including ciders) on tap. Revived our love of this place when my husband and I started eating vegan! Always delicious and so friendly.

name: Mercato Ristorante
address: 111 Market St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Mercato is a casual restaurant with good food and decent wines. The staff are outgoing and accommodating. The food and service is very consistent.
The best value is the Kitchen Dinner served Sunday through Thursday 5 to close for $25. It's a 3 course meal with a good variety of choices for appetizers, entrees and dessert. 
Happy hour is 3 to 5 daily. 
I have personally had the pork tenderloin, the ravioli, the penne, and the the tagliatelle and all were excellent. The pear and Gorgonzola salad is very good.

Went here during lunch around 2pm.  Sat outside on their spacious patio with umbrellas it was very nice. Check in with host to be seated outside. Service was perfect, prompt, professional and knowledgable.  They also have happy hour from 3 to 5 every day. We will be back to try the kitchen dinner 3 course meal.

Never a bad meal at this unique Italian restaurant. If you can wiggle your way into Skylar's section, he will make your experience even better. These people provide excellent food while doing it with panache!
My go-to restaurant. Great appetizers, entrees, pasta, pizza and of course desserts. Outdoor patio when it's warm outside, lots of free parking. Love this place!
I’ve been here for quite a few team dinners. I like their cocktail options. It’s just that they have very limited vegetarian options. It’d be great if they can accommodate that in their menu.

name: Dirty Dave's Pizza Parlor
address: 3939 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews:
The images shows how delicious the pizza smelled when it was delivered to our table. It was half gone by the time I could take the shot.
We had a great time with only two pieces left.
When I asked for foil for the two pieces, the server asked if it was going to be a late night snack. I told him that I'm a homeless advocate and the leftover was going to a man who has eaten virtually nothing but ramen for the last week.
B4 we left, the server gave us a "mistake" to add to the food we were handing out.
So instead of feeding one, we feed three.

Dirty Dave's is a genuine old-time pizza parlor, where you can find affordable pizza, beer, sandwiches, pasta.   Atmosphere is comfy and casual.
A great spot for a quiet private party!

Parking is ample and free.

The best pizza place in the area, by far. The classic pizzas use a thin crust, melty cheese, offer numerous toppings (including cashews), and are always delicious. The "3D pizza" is a pseudo Chicago Style pizza that really lives up to being a "Pizza Pie".

They do offer other food, such as pasta, but I've never wanted to get anything but their pizza.
Get the family deluxe pasta bowl.  Huge portion as you can see for yourself.    Pizza is also delicious.
Staple of Olympia.  Best pizza around in my opinion!! Sandwiches (The Jake) amazing. Salad bar, best around! Employee's are great and great family spot.

name: Rush In Alaskan Dumplings
address: 205 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Came here for the happy hour and was not disappointed. We had a beer and dozen dumplings. The beer was Alaskan Amber, so they don’t skimp on the promo. The dumplings we had were the Buffalo and Classic. They were both delicious with tons of flavor. The dumpling dough is thicker than other dumplings, but that wasn’t an issue. The sauces/broths were amazing, but we wish there was more bread served to soak it up! 

Overall, this is a great stop in downtown Oly that deserves your business. The gentleman who took our order was super nice and very attentive. He was the cook, cashier, and I’m sure everything else. Kudos to him!

Took my daughter for dinner. The menu looks big on the board but it's really not. I like the simplicity. They could have a few more side choices. Didn't get one this time. We ordered the 18 dumpling option. The cook/one man show let me split it so we got two choices of filling. Daughter picked cheese and potato and I picked pork and beef. We both picked the loaded option for our toppings. I tried a couple dipping sauces. The garlic was too bitter (I love garlic). The Sriracha dip was better. Very filling for a great price. Seating is limited to about six or eight tables. Some are for two people. I'll go back.

-Okay first off, so delicious. Everything. Every combination, everything. Yum yum! 
-Second, they'll mix and match fillings for you. It's like a surprise with every bite. Woohoo!!! 
-Third, such good service! The guy behind the counter is so polite, brings you food and drinks, and really appears to care about your experience. And his accent was beautiful.
-Last but not least - the upstairs is delightfully warm and cozily lit. Which is fantastic in winter when you want to melt into a chair with your bowl of warm and cozy dumplings. 
EAT HERE!!!!

This place was amazing! Such a cute and cozy place for starters. The food was also really, really good. Good portions for the price and the dumplings were tender and flavorful. I had the loaded chicken dumplings and it had just the right amount of sweet and savory. Definitely one of my favorite spots to go to now!

This place is incredible! First, the owner is so kind and warm. Second, we ordered two rounds of food because it was so heavenly. We ended up getting the classic dumplings with pork and beef, the buffalo with chicken, and the Alaskan as a mix of everything. This is the perfect local spot to have an incredible experience!

name: Wayside Cafe and Deli
address: 609 Capitol Way S, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Quaint and cozy location with delicious plant based meals. Plenty of different varieties from sandwich’s to bowls. From simple to complex something for everyone to enjoy. Local brews and kombucha available. Small made house desert options too.

I love so many of their dishes. I could go on and on. My super favorite is their Cajun Chicken sandwich with a gluten free bun. So many gluten free choices like swapping their gravy with  cheese sauce on top of your mash potatoes and Mac and cheese!! Thank you Way side for making vegan gluten free available and deliciously fantastic!

Fantastic tasting food, and i can't wait to go back to try more. I got the rib plate and all the sides were great. They were out of the mashed potatoes so i did the house slaw instead.  It was rather noisy from a fan but other than that it was a good experience, and it was very comforting not having to ask to make changes to the menu just to keep it plant based/vegan.

Yum! Tried the rib plate, and it was delicious, and worth the wait. The portion size was good because I was pretty full after eating. I'm not vegan myself, but I like trying vegan dishes when I feel like it. Of course I wasn't expecting the texture to be the same as a real rib, but it was yummy nonetheless. I'd say maybe more salt in the mac n cheese, but perhaps I just like salt too much. Lol. I'll be back for the sweets and "wings".

The almost famous bowl was delicious and exactly what I was looking for. My family isn't vegan but thoroughly enjoyed everything we had. The staffed was nice and extremely helpful. Our food came out very quickly after we ordered. The only thing I may not order again was the potato bites . The Mac and cheese was phenomenal 👌

name: Arepa Latin Street Food
address: 728 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Amazing food, carne arepa was great and really loved the tostones. It was very filling and it priced just right...

I spent several years of my youth living in Venezuela in the late 70's.  I miss that food and Arepa gives me a bit of a taste of it, without having to risk my life going to Venezuela current day.  Cant say it is as good as when I was a kid, but my tastebuds today are much more profound than they were 40 years ago... Arepa is good, give it a shot.

Food here was amazing, fresh, and very fast (though to be honest there was only one order ahead of me). Did the moderna puerco, very very tasty, pork was perfect. completely satisfied and the price was reasonable. If I lived in Olympia I would definitely be back at least once a week.
I can’t believe I’m just discovering this food truck. I’m in love with their food. Escpically having a choice of sale or burrito for my favorite flavor. Portions are generous

Carne arepa was good. The bread could have been a little more toasty in my opinion, but it was good regardless. Costs $8 but does have a lot of meat inside. Tasted like carnitas, which I love. The fried plantains were good too.

name: Brewery City Pizza Lacey
address: 4353 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98516, USA
reviews: Very glad to have found this place. The pizza is really good. Hard to find a good pepperoni pizza in this town. Fair price and best I've found since they took one of my favorites away.. Will be returning for more..

Great place to go out to dinner. From the amazing and friendly staff to the equally amazing food, you can't go wrong. I highly recommend the Athenian and Brewery City pizza. The Brewzer calzone was also a clear winner tonight.

Cauliflower crust pizza was delicious!! I got the meat one with extra cheese and extra sauce and it was amazing!  Also i was hesitant to order the medium because i was going to share with coworkers but it fed 6 people

Had it delivered.  $23.00 for a “medium” pizza!   It was supposed to be a large for $17.00.   We ordered half with onions, pineapple, and mushrooms, and the other half with just onions and pineapple (no mushrooms) they charged us twice for the pineapple ($5.00 total) and twice for the onions ($2.00 total) almost eight bucks for some skimpy toppings.  overall a ho-hum pizza. And If that’s their medium, I’d hate to see a small. Never again

Just discovered this beautiful gem in lacey.   Our experience was awesome.  One of the best cesar salads i ever had.  Very reasonably priced.    The pida bread that was served with my tomato basil soup was delicious.    I will definitely be coming to try their giant pizzas.   Our calzone was to die for.    Great job guys.    We will see you again soon.    Oh they have Happy hour also.   Take advantage of it.   Just awesome guys.

name: Martin Way Diner
address: 2423 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: Great locally-owned small greasy spoon diner.  Breakfast all day and open til 9pm. Friendly, casual staff. Lots of scratch tickets too, if you're into that! Great for kids.  Probably a good idea to call ahead if you have a large party.

I had the All-American Breakfast and I was very surprised at the large portions of food that came out for the price. All the food was great and I left with a stuffed belly. The staff was also very friendly and helpful. Great spot local for Sunday brunch!

It is always friendly with good service.  Popular place especially with many of the local seniors.  Has good music playing in the background but not so loud that you and everyone else in the restaurant have to talk extra loud to carry on a conversation with each other. Had the fish and chips.  The fish was crispy and well done.  The fries were good but nothing to write home about.  The coleslaw was a bit on the warm side on being served and wasn't very flavorful.  It was warm enough I was dubious about eating it so after a couple bites I figured better safe than sorry so didn't eat it.  Overall all was good and would certainly go again.

Busy with locals. Menu was hard to order from. I wanted something fresh and it had a canned feel to it. Too landlocked to order seafood. Only had breakfast but not on my list to try again. Cinnamon roll french toast was great.
I loved this place, the burger I got was amazing and cooked perfect. If your looking to support a local business this is definitely a place to go. Great food and fast service.

name: Fujiyama Japanese Steakhouse
address: 2930 Capital Mall Dr SW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: It doesn't matter if you make reservations, if it's not a big enough party to fill a whole table you will end up waiting. The cook we had was really funny and a great showman. The food was perfectly cooked, we had chicken, steak, shrimp and the lobster, which was not really fishy. Had one of the house mixed drinks which I would say was blah, stick with beer or wine. Would return.
Best birthday experience! Uncle BJ is amazing!! Cant wait to come back. Best atmosphere, amazing food and the an unbelievable chef!

This rating has nothing to do with the cook who prepared our food. He was great, we even left him a nice tip. Unfortunately we won't be back because the hostess was so rude. We literally almost walked out because of her attitude. I understand it was Sunday and they were busy. We did have a reservation and we were sat 30 minutes after our reservation time. Still no big deal but the way she interacted with not only us, but everyone else was uncalled for. I even smiled at her twice. She literally rolled her eyes lol. Obviously she doesn't know how to manage a floor or reservations and shouldn't be working with people. My family had another reservation for 2 weeks from today and we've just cancelled it. The bathroom smells horrible too.
We had a great time. Food was good and the chef was very entertaining.
Great food and entertaining cook. The fried rice is tasty and you get a large portion. You can't miss on anything on the menu. You should leave very full. A little pricey but well worth it.

name: Sushi House
address: 2000 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia, WA 98512, USA
reviews: I came here cause our usual sushi place was closed early. Best decision ever! This is about the best sushi I've ever had. Plating is beautiful, good quality food, impeccable service, great atmosphere. All around a fabulous experience. If you like sushi or Japanese style food, come here.

My absolute favorite sushi restaurant. I used to live close, but now it's a 3 hour drive to get there,  but I've made the drive several times.  I love it that much.  The crispy avocado appetizer and the dynamite rolls are to die for!  They're consistently fantastic! I cannot recommend this place highly enough.
I was not expecting much, but I got hungry. Service and food was outstanding. It has a light and airy feel to the restaurant.

So amazingly good!!!!

The scallop dynamite roll is absolutely delicious. Many rolls and appetizers were ordered. All fantastic. 

Baked teriyaki salmon was great. 

Everything was amazing. 

Service wasn't great, but the food and atmosphere was so good I'm giving them 5 stars anyway.
This is the best Japanese restaurant in Olympia (in my opinion) Excellent service. Excellent food. Just all around a must go to if you're a sushi lover!

name: Hotstone Authentic Korean Cuisine
address: 119 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Hotstone offers some amazing Korean dishes in downtown Olympia. With outstanding customer service and an inviting environment, this restaurant is perfect for a solo experience or large groups. I was very impressed with their portion sizes and attention to detail.
Easily one of the best restaurants in town. Hot, perfectly balanced dishes. I've enjoyed all the many items I have ordered here. The food is savory and comforting.

Wow just wow. The most authentic Korean food I have ever had. The server was very nice and professional. Also very respectful. I felt like I was in Korea having a meal. I would highly recommend this place for their food and service. I will definitely be back.
Heavenly Beef Bulgogi.  All the sides come with. Sweet savory with classic spice.  If this place was in my hometown I'd never eat at home!!!
I didn't realize Hotstone meant hot food. Very tasty, delicious and any other adjective you might want to use describe this wonderful place

name: Koibito Sushi Japanese Restaurant
address: 1707 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Our favorite sushi place in Olympia. Every time we go we are served quickly. They have our favorite rolls and have good service. They are usually busy however and the restaurant is small. Not a good place for large groups but they'll make up a table for you.

Very friendly wait staff and high quality sushi. I absolutely love the wide variety of sushi that they offer. They have a very detailed menu so that those who are new to sushi understand what they are ordering. They always offer a cup of miso soup while you are waiting for your meal. The sushi is always fresh and beautifully placed with wasabi and ginger on the side for flavor. If you want the full experience I would highly recommend ordering the chefs choice. It's a surprise variety. These pictures were also taken after I had traded my friend two of our sushi pieces so it doesnt look as pretty as it did when I first received the plate. If you love sushi or are new to sushi I definitely recommend coming here for an all around delightful meal. They also offer a wide variety of non sushi cuisine. I have had several other non sushi dishes there and am constantly pleased with the quality of the food. Definitely recommend 100%.
Very good. Surprisingly good. I came in for lunch and MAN it was good. Service was FANTASTIC. I will definitely be back and i am definitely recommending this place!!!

Kenny is the champion of sushi in Olympia.  All you need to know:  he takes fresh albacore, soaks it in a garlic/black pepper marinade of his own creation, and then casually places it on the menu for true sushi aficionados to spot.  You will not find this type of attention paid to most fish, let alone sushi on the west coast.  And yet a diamond in the rough awaits you at Koibito.
Best sashimi I have ever had and the beef teriyaki bento was awesome,def going there for lunch again.

name: Vics Pizzeria
address: 233 Division St NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Best New York style pizza in the county. Fold in half,start from the point. Always friendly staff,always clean. Perfect chewy crust, wide variety of toppings, great selection for slices to go. Order in with a pint,good IPA choice too. This place earned the 5 star.

Nice place. They have whole pizzas and also pizza by the slice. Been here a few times and the staff is always friendly and the pizza is always good. They have some beer on tap, as well as crater lake root beer. Also like that there is a coffee to sit either inside or outside. The pizza is this crust and the slices are big, so if you have kids, you'll have to cut them smaller. Overall it's always a good place to eat.

Really good pizza. It's a small little place, but usually pretty quiet, you order your pizza at the counter and they bring it to you. You get your own drinks. A pretty classic pizza place with delicious pizza.

Easily the best all around pizza place in Olympia.  I have introduced many people to Vic's and once they try it they are hooked.  Don't sleep on the Vegan slices, meat eaters, vegetarians, and vegans all can agree that the vegan pizzas hold their own.  Fantastic flavors and creativity.

Remember the pizza you used to eat, that was so amazing????
Vic's still makes it!!
Plus you can buy a slice, and they always have some great vegan pizza slices.  It's informal dining , and it can be noisy at lunch or dinner time,  but it's a true neighborhood hangout,  and if the locals love it,  you might, too.....

name: Kizuki Ramen & Izakaya
address: 120 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Good food as always but called and made a reservation for 5pm. It was confirmed with the person who took my call. We arrived early, but were told our reservation was at 5:30. On their books it looked like they had scribbled out 5 to put 5:30.
The food was wonderful as always, but their customer service left something to be desired.

This place is great. Happy hour everyday from 4:30-6:39 and all day Sunday. The menu has types of ramen, rice dishes, and appetizers. My husband and I definitely enjoyed our time. Just know that you can't use Kizuki gift cards here only local sold gift certificates.
Yes it isn't cheap, bit you get what you pay for. A wonderful environment, friendly staff, and delicious food. If you enjoy sake... Try to get to know the owner... Just saying... Thank me later

Delicious ramen, had the garlic chicken one. Will be going back and can't wait to warm up my leftovers! If you eat all the noodles but still have broth you can ask for more noodles which is great! Can't wait to go back!

Wow!! That is THE best Ramen I have ever had! Get the Garlic broth with pork belly. The egg in it was amazing! They marinate it for 12 hours before soft boiling it. Crazy good flavor! Even the bamboo shoots are something special! The squid was the bomb too! Will definitely be coming back. I read about the service being crappy, bull!! they were ALL sweet as can be! Even the chefs.

name: The Mark Olympia
address: 407 Columbia St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Amazing food! The steak was a little tough but very tasty. Has to be one of the best  chicken dishes I've ever had. Staff were very friendly. This is no $$ place tho. This is more like $$$$. Dinner for two with two cocktails and a glass of wine came out to 110$. Very tasty tho.
Really good food and drinks. Would recommend.
Fantabulous food and service. Healthiest menu with local & organic meals.

Great find on our way to Seattle. Limited menu but everything is on point. Wish pasta came with an option for meat but the flavors  are all there and locally sourced. Indoors has a weird setup but upscale.outdoor patio is chill and relaxing. Definately worth a try!
Such an amazing dinner. The food is so fresh, flavorful and superbly prepared. The owner only selects what's in season and delicious. We had a wonderful evening. Thank you ❤

name: Eastside Big Tom
address: 2023 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: The atmosphere was really awesome especially on a cooler summer day. The burger was better than McDonald’s but still nothing to rave about. That goo sauce reminds me of deviled eggs and kind of tastes like it too. The fries are like the ones you got as a kid for school lunch (not good) my husband got a chocolate shake it wasn’t stirred well they just pour chocolate syrup in, I got a banana milk shake it was not good. I would not go back. The lady at the burger stand was way more personable than the ladies who work at the main house or pay area where we got the milkshakes

It had been over 30 years since I had a Big Tom's Burger. I'm thinking the last time was with my daddy, when I lived near there in 1981, before moving to Seattle. Now, I'm back in town, hit up Big Tom's and they make a great burger. If you're looking for just a simple but satisfying burger, minus all the extra mess, then Big Tom's is the place. Friendly staff, ready to assist you, and great strawberry shakes.
The double burger was pretty good. The parking lot was insane though. Cars everywhere. The staff was really friendly. Might try eating here again when they are serving off their regular menu.

Big Tom's is an Olympia original. I arrived during a peak rush about 6pm. There was a line backing up onto the street. My eyes instantly met the eyes of an employee directing me out of the line and to a parking area. The service was prompt, friendly and attentive. I didn't even wait long- even with the line. I saw employees scurrying about. All were engaged with customers. The Big Tom, tots, goop and milkshake were all yummy and live up to the reputation! Service and food both get thumbs up! Its a great drive through and worth your visit!

Food was great. And I loved the atmosphere. My girls loved the dinosaurs! 
I'd love to come back next time I'm in the area.

name: Da Nang Restaurant
address: 116 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: First time here and we will definitely be eating here again. I enjoyed the walnut chicken and will get it again. I will also be getting their walnut shrimp. Nice and friendly atmosphere and our waiter was great. They also do a punch card here so that is a major bonus. You buy a meal and get a stamp fill up the card and get a free meal.

I love Danang. They have a full and unique menu. The biggest thing I appreciate about danang is there vegan and vegetarian options if you are looking for meatless.  Service is not overly attentive but always correct.  They have delicious hum bow and the yellow seafood curry is amazing!

I used to be a huge fan. Lately, I've ordered delivery from this restaurant. I recently made a comment to my partner that Da Nang seems to be messing up our orders more frequently than not.

On the last few occasions, I ordered vegetarian "almond chicken," which comes with deep friend imitation chicken and a sort of almond sauce to drizzle over the almond crumbles.

The sauce they've delivered is clearly old, as if they've made it earlier in the week and kept it refrigerated. However, the sauce is beyond edible and has separated into a sort of hard lump of almond and smelly old oil.  On top of receiving old, curdled almond sauce, I've received congealed peanut sauce for the spring rolls. I have a feeling they are not cleaning out their refrigerator as frequently as they should.

In addition to the gross sauces, the new delivery guy seems to chain smoke with the windows up in his car while delivering the food, leaving the food and packaging with a very strong stench of cigarette smoke.

I'm not someone to leave bad reviews. I've given them at least 5 chances. Unfortunately, I no longer have an appetite for Da Nang. Dine-in if you eat here, so you can see the food before paying.

The restaurant itself was clean and had a calming, peaceful atmosphere. The food was amazing. Since moving back to Olympia from the Seattle area two years ago, we've been looking for a great bowl of pho...found it. The spring roll was so delicious to the point my daughter tried it and loved it. This a must visit.

Great service by staff, food was ok.
Phở broth wasn't hot enough to cook the rare beef
Chili oil was really spicy and good. The chow fun and hone walnut shrimp was delicious.

name: Hash
address: 1807 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Made it to Hash for Breakfast with friends. The food was amazing; so many mimosa choices. When they say the pancake is big enough to share; they mean it. Refer to the picture of my friends with his pancake for scale. Everything that we had was great. I will definitely go back.

I got the chicken fried steak and my husband got the cornbread hash and our daughter got the pancakes. We waited an hour to be seated at 11, the chicken fried steak tasted funny not like in the south, the cornbread was like cake, the server was nice but not attentive there were people waiting standing up watching us which is awkward. The cornbread and pink butter was good, toast was good, eggs were good. It was $50 for breakfast which seemed extremely expensive

AMAZING!!! Every item on the menu is fresh and delicious! The service is wonderful, very sweet and caring people! It's also family friendly. We love it there. It's our go-to breakfast restaurant after mass every Sunday!

For the price, and the wait, should've gone somewhere else. The place has good food. I ordered the corned beef hash. The potatoes and hash browns were good. I even enjoyed the eggs, and the sour dough bread was amazing. The corn bread was too sweet for me, reminding me more of yellow cake. My 6 year old loved it, and kept calling the spread that came with it "frosting". Like I said, the place is good, but it took an hour to even sit. It's better than IHOP, but I was just done with the whole experience by the time I got seated.

Excellent everything! The food is amazing! The staff is friendly and fast!  The ambiance is welcoming and earthy. Even the other patrons were friendly and talkative!  
If you like pancakes,  you have to order the monstrous blueberry and pistachio...OMG! 
All around nice place to eat and enjoy a great meal. The price is a bit spendy but definitely worth it! My husband and I had breakfast "a whole lot to eat" for about 50.00

name: Far East
address: 218 4th Ave W, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Just a quick public review! 
Thai Restaurant: Far East in the heart of down town Olympia! 
I want this little husband and wife restaurant to have more exposure because they don’t advertise at all and I LOVE them! 
I religiously order 
1. Pad Thai w/ tofu
2. Veggie Delight w/ tofu
3. Broccoli w/beef 
4. Thai Tea! Best one I’ve ever ordered! 
YUM! 
The wife has the best customer service, memorized all of my favorite orders and is just full of amazing energy, and her husband is the best cook! 
I’ve had other Thai food and yes it’s good but other places over sauce or use some sauces my tummy does not like, but they keep it fresh, simple, light, and delicious! 
10/10 my favorite place to get lunch!
A quick, flavorful, fresh and affordable. Stopped in here on the way through town. Would definitely return.. yum!

I'm in love with this secret food destination.
Always fresh and delicious. Friendlier than any other place in town.

I have been eating at Far East since 2009, and cannot speak highly enough about the food and service here - both have been exemplary at *every single visit* for over a decade. What more can you ask for, truly, in a restaurant?  

Visit, enjoy, and tell your friends - Far East is the way to go :D

A great little family restaurant in downtown. My family has been going here for years now and this place never disappoints. I can't recommend them enough to anybody looking for some great, quality food in Olympia.

name: Mekong Thai Restaurant
address: 125 Columbia St NW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Got the food to-go, and can say it was a fast and great experience. From ordering in person till I was in my car driving away was a total of about 15 minutes, and while I waited inside it was a pleasant experience with good art pieces and a clean calm environment. The Mekong egg rolls and Phud Thai were the best I’ve eaten. The Mekong curry was also good and very spicy. I will definitely be eating here again.

Very delicious food! Such large portions and not expensive. We ordered Combo #1 (egg roll, vegetarian pad Thai, rice, sautéed veggies and chicken) and Combo #2 (egg roll, vegetarian pad Thai, rice, curry). It was so much food we had very full take home containers. But everything was delicious! We’ll definitely stop here again next time we pass through Olympia.

Delicious!  Attentive to our needs, and fair prices, this amazing restaurant has been a favorite for years!  Plenty of options for people with special diets, including gluten free, vegetarian, and vegan! Also plenty of meaty and seafood items for the omnivores and pescatarians!
Love me some green curry! I think I’ve found my new favorite spot. It was clean + quite environment for a quick lunch. Service was prompt. My order came out quick.
Great spot in downtown Olympia. Love the curry and the fried wontons.

name: Seed & Bloom Plant-Based Kitchen
address: 500 Capitol Way S, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Every single thing here is delicious. The people are so nice. The space is wonderful for hanging out, visiting, working. Can't say enough good things about them! My fave items are the scones, breakfast sandwiches, Italian melt, and the spicy peanut wrap!

Just ate here for the first time and really enjoyed my Italian melt sandwich 👍!  I dig Olympia's vegan catering eateries.  All the folks working at Seed and Bloom were nice 🙏!  There is a small selection of vegan cheeses/butters/milks and some other goodies like bags of vegan chips that you can get there as well.  I picked some Miyoko's butter and cheddar spread while there, the old lady and I enjoy those products 🤙  Check it out and support local businesses 🙌
a LIL pricey but not too bad. REALLY GOOD tasty vegan deli-type food. had a curry potato salad that blew my mind! thanks so much to the artisans creating these great treats!

Nutritious and flavorful, this shop is a delight to go to. This elegant location is the ideal place for a large range of diets such as vegan, vegetarian, etc. They carry wine, beer, organic drinks, and smorgasbord of salads and sandwich options.
Best coffee ever ...didn't even add sweetener (Olympia Coffee Roasting Company). Awesome music. Awesome service. Excellent prices. $2.75 for 20 oz or two refills on 8 oz mug eat in.

name: Izzy's
address: 3540 Pacific Ave SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: The owner and his wife do an excellent job. The food is great and Rosa and Gloria are our favorite employees. They give a 150 percent all the time. You can't be in better hands than Rosa's and Gloria's. Enjoy the food and atmosphere. Enjoy yourself!

Here now!  Was invited by the owner to eat and share the experience.  Busy, helpful, cheerful, hardworking staff.👍👍👍👍👍  Clean, tasty, well stocked, fresh, did I mention clean?  Fried chicken was amazing, (tender and juicy).   Baked beans amazing (great smoky taste).  The corn lacked in seasonings but it was tender and sweet.👍👍👍  The salad bar was as it should be, clean, fresh, well stocked and not over loaded with too many choices but just right. I drove down from Puyallup and will do it many times over for this place.  I'd recommend Izzy's to anyone who has ever eaten at other American buffets.  The price is so low for what you're getting!  On demand, all you can eat sirloin steak, prepared any way you like and batter fried fish or fish tacos made to order.  Do it, visit this place, you'll come back, guaranteed.
I have never been disappointed with this amazing restaurant! The staff is so great. I love to see that the same employees have worked there forever! The food is good and lots of variety!
Delicious food, staff is always friendly and helpful.. we love it here! We drive from an hour away to to Izzys.. I eat seafood now because of their cod like no lie

DELIVERY and CARRY-OUT?! Yes, please! We were thrilled to find one of our favs open for business. This is a great go-to when we can't stand our own food anymore (this happens a lot). Great service, people and food!

name: El Sarape
address: 955 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: After a rough start, we had a wonderful night. It was my husbands birthday and there was 14 of us to be seated, we did find seating for all of us in a long set of tables. Our server, Romero, who's birthday it was tonight also, was magnificent. He served us by himself, no one ever had to wait on a thing, he was there for us.  No mistake was made. Thankyou very much.

Spent all day in remodel, wanted an easy meal. Ordered on door dash, received ordered meal with chips and salsa. First awesome discovery. Second awesome, the meal came with recyclable containers! Yes!! Third, is was so so good! My husbands vegan, he couldn’t believe I didn’t order him a regular chicken dish. It was all so good! Ordered a verde burrito, avacado enchilada, and a side veggie tamale. Can’t wait to order again - amazing!! El Sarape, looking forward to when we can visit you in person until then... door dash!

Delicious. Most dishes between 15-25 dollars and totally worth it. Had some chips and salsa to start with and that itself was really good. We had the fiesta dinner and fajita trio. It was amazing! We loved it.

This is my first time going here since the building was the black bear diner. They took the building and built a gorgeous restaurant! The decor, the tables, the back of the bar, and even a round table around a fire!? I was hands down impressed when I compared this location to the old El Sarape! 
The food was also great, we ordered 2 different taco plates and both were good! The avocado salsa that came with them was just right and delicious! The drinks were also good and fast (we were in the bar but that doesn't always equal good or fast). Lastly we fed 2 adults with margaritas for less than $50! 
If you didn't like the old place, make sure you gice this one a shot, you won't be dissappointed!

Delicious food! Great place for a date. Lots of good vegan options. Avocado enchiladas are amazing! Convenient take out. At the bar they have a great happy hour with fresh tasty chips and house salsa.

name: Fish Tale Brewpub
address: 515 Jefferson St SE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Always good food, fresh and delicious. Brews to choose from Leavenworth to their own home variety, plenty of seating, located in downtown Olympia.

It was packed! Which I like to see means that it’s a good place to eat. Had the Fish tacos and sweet potato fries. It was delicious, we ordered food and it was out in no time! Great service and Fantastic Food. Definitely a must go!

I liked this place and think that they had a good selection! I tried a couple of the IPAs and was not disappointed!!! The staff were very nice, friendly, and helpful in selecting beers, the food was good as well! We had the public house  burger and they cooked it to order! We also had the tater tots which were impressive from someone coming from the Midwest! The place was fairly spacious, with indoor and outdoor seating and a pretty sizable indoor area. This place had good ambiance and overall great place to stop for a beer and food!!

Great selection of beer from a classic WA brewpub.  I enjoyed each of my 4 samples.  The imperial IPA with honey notes (Hodgson’s Imperial IPA) was the standout for me.  Their nachos were excellent with plenty to go around for a group.  The venue is huge but in need of some interior investment.  Super nice and attentive staff!
Delicious!! The fish basket is enormous. Perfectly fried cod and oysters. Plenty of beer and cider on tap to choose from. Service is friendly and the atmosphere is inviting!

name: State & Central
address: 1415 State Ave NE, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: I was in Olympia for a night and we decided to get some burgers at this place. The service was phenomenal! I wish I remembered ladies that attended us there, because they were incredibly nice! The food itself left me satisfied and reminded me of what a good quality burger should taste like. The burger itself was super juicy (I got the 'Juicy Lucy' so it lived up to its name). Overall, my experience here was great and if I find myself in Olympia again, this will be the first place I visit!

I've been several times and always enjoyed the meals. Menu has something for most diners. It's largely pub fair done well, burgers, fish and chips, salads, etc... Everything I've tried was good.
Looked like 8-12 taps and a variety of styles of beer as well as a full bar.
It's a small spot so there may be a wait during busy hours. There is some outside seating as weather permits.

Don't wait, stop in. Street parking may be tough at busy times. Fast friendly service, clean and efficient.  I only had fish and chips -excellent light and crispy beer batter and thin cut fries, coleslaw was very good also. There is a nice selection of brews and wine. The restroom was very clean. I will be back for more.
Absolutely L.O.V.E.  this place!  Limited parking, so take advantage of the easy access by bike.   Best tomato bisque in Oly.

Great food as usual although I would desire another choice of potatoes for breakfast other than tots or fries and a better choice of toast.  For lunch or dinner no one beats S&C but they need to make the same commitment to breakfast that they do to dinner.  The omelette was awesome, my partner's bacon looked amazing, good coffee, just need to step up their game with home fries and toast.

name: King Solomon's Reef
address: 212 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Absolutely perfect! Like everything about everything was so good! I had the biggest side of mashed potatoes and gravy in my life and it was probably the second greatest joy of my life. I have a kid so ya know. But for real do yourself and your whole table a favor and get them mashed potatoes! They are life changing. We also got the BLAT which was delicious and a grilled cheese with the tomato soup that was to die for.
King Solomon's Reef Restaurant has some of THE best tasting and high quality breakfast foods at reasonable and affordable prices. The service is top notch!
Food is delicious and fresh.  Will definitely coming back.    Great service also.   Good job guys.

This is Bryan. I wanted to write this review and give credit due where it's due. I haven't been here to this place in 3 years. I'm temporarily here for a month and wanted to stop in and have a few beers. There is a Barkeep here named John. He is what makes this Bar. It's a decent place to go if you want to just chill lay back and get your thoughts together. You won't meet a more real good hearted good guy than John. The folks here are awesome and they have great food etc.
  We need to as Americans support our good little American bars and Cafes. Thumbs up to The Reef. Also to John the Main Barkeep glad we have good Men like this around. Let's Support Our American Buusinesses🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸👍👍👍

Love to eat here, best homemade biscuits, big, and fluffy, melts in your mouth, just like my Great Grandma made. Great place for everyone, vegetarian, and vegan food available. If you haven't been there yet, you have to go as soon as possible.

name: Narai Asian Cuisine
address: 320 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: They're still open for takeout during the shutdown! The food is delicious. My order was filled in less than ten minutes (although I was the only one ordering in person at the time). They were so gracious and gave me a stamp card for free crispy egg rolls on my 6th order. The chicken pad Thai was a sufficient spicy at a level two, came with fresh carrots, sprouts, and crushed peanuts! Will definitely be back.
Super friendly owner and chef wife. Feels like home cooking. Delicious food flavors! Good variety, quick service, easy on the pocket too!
Great place. Great service. Really high quality, fresh ingredients and authentic recipes.

We stopped in late one night to grab some food to go. The owner promptly greeted us and took our order. He was helpful and our food was ready super fast. The salad rolls were fresh and they came with two delicious sauces to dip them in. Our main courses were fresh and steaming hot in our togo boxes. At home we feasted and decided that Narai is the only place to get Thai in Oly.
Gracious hosts. Good fried rice. Narai temple is nice

name: Octapas Cafe
address: 414 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Great place. The venues bar and staff was great and the bands who played last night were exceptional!

Octapas is a warm and welcoming place to meet a friend or a group or family. Full bar, coffee bar, and desserts, with the best ginger carrot cake one can consume. There are live events in the black box at the rear of the restaurant. You'll find yourself in the heart of Olympia community. The food is imaginative and , specializing in tapas, with entrees to soothe a hungry soul. Vegan options is an understatement. Check out their website!
What a hidden gem. The menu is exciting.  The food is delicious.  The prices are extremely reasonable.  And the ambience is wonderful for a date night. I highly recommend.
Friendly service even while quiet. Looks like it would be really fun during live entertainment. Interesting tapas menu.

This is my first giving a review ever on a restaurant.
I ordered a dish that highlighted Oysters on their menu. I was excited and ready to enjoy the dish. When I was served I had to really look around for the 2-medium size Oysters. I was expecting a dish that was focused on oysters, more than 2 anyway. That was very disappointing to me. Don't put the word oysters in the description and serve a dish with 2 Oysters! The dish fell short ☹️ due to the lack of them, in my option.

name: Cooper Point Public House
address: 3002 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: I absolutely love Cooper Point Public House! It has a warm and rustic charm from the moment you walk in all the way down to the food presentation. It's menu while small still has something of value for everyone. I can honestly say they have the best and I mean THE BEST buttermilk pancakes EVER! Lunch is great too! I also love their sustainability focus, by locally sourcing, composting, and utilizing paper straws. Let's not forget the staff who work hard to provide you with a fabulous experience, quick service, suggestions, and a kind smile.

The atmosphere is nice enough but the food was a bit off. I had the bacon, egg, pub potatoes and pancakes with a Dr. Pepper. The bacon was okay. Egg, scrambled was a bit tasteless. The potatoes tasted like they should have been tossed out due to being past their prime. The pancakes, although smelled wonderful, reminded me more of a custard or flan. They just didn’t taste like good ole hot cakes. Everything just seemed lacking in flavor

Excellent bar food and fast service.  I went
with a group at happy hour and the menu choices was very good.  So was the
price, if you go try the fried pickles and
wings.  If you just want to eat good fried food, at a quiet no nonsense restaurant, this is a great place for you.

Innocuous interior with no "public house" feel. Food was adequate,  and I would go again to try other menu items. I had a skillet breakfast and it was decent but lacked pizzazz. "Toast" was not buttered and was little more than dried bread with no color or toasting on it.
Wait staff was friendly and efficient. 
Definitely worth a try, could be a good place, just need to dial it in a bit on what they're trying to be with food and atmosphere.
Good food in a laid back atmosphere. Wait staff has always been friendly and our orders have been accurate. Service times can be a bit slow so leave yourself some time to relax and enjoy :)

name: Saigon Rendezvous ( Pho Na )
address: 117 5th Ave SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Such a great spot. Our server was very friendly, there wasn’t a long wait. Food tasted great. I ordered the beef meatball Pho and it was amazing!!! I legit recommend this place!

I was craving a warm soup and decided to try this place. I was pleasantly surprised. The food was incredibly delicious. It tasted clean, meaning they dont go crazy with the salt and im pretty sure they don't use msg. The service is kind and friendly.

I went here before but didn't know it had changed owners, the surprise was more than pleasant, it was awesome!  The host is the most gracious of any place in town. The food is fresh. I mean vegetables probably purchased today. They only cares if everything was great and that you have everything you want. I will definitely go back, I'll probably bring my whole family next time. Looking forward to buying this from Uber eats.
Tasty food, service is slow but nice people.
Great food and great service!

name: Thai Garden Restaurant-Lounge
address: 2735 Harrison Ave NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Love this Thai place and so do my friends!  We were looking for a casual place for a nice lunch together.  There were a few other groups of friends doing the same thing.  Food is fresh, lots of veggies and it doesn't take very long.  Staff is friendly too, good ambiance with the plants in the room.

The food tasted like it was made days ago and just reheated. The server was asked for lemon when she did our drink order and we never received them till asking when she finally checked on us half way through the meal. The rice dishes were extremely dry and even with lots of soy sauce, still taste less. Sadly I will not eat here again!!!

What a wonderful ambience. The service was fast, the food was delicious. We can their hot wings and spicy fried dumplings for an appetizer. Followed by a vegetarian and non vegetarian entree. Both were delicious and served with a side of rice. Definitely worth the $12.50 we paid for them. The Thai iced coffees were delicious as well. The fish tank was cool for the kids too look at during the short wait for our food. All the plants were nice to look at as well. I highly recommend going in just after noon. Very chill.

This is a top notch eating establishment. With authentic Thai food and drink.  Prices are moderate but not overly expensive. The waitstaff is knowledgeable and friendly and Everything tasted wonderful.  Enjoy

I have worked in the restaurant industry for many years. I had been to Thai garden multiple times but today I had a bad experience... it was little things that added up that I usually let slide because I am a server myself. But this time I really felt like they don’t know about good customer service policies:
1.) we walked in and weren’t greeted...there were 2 tables and no employees in the front of the house to be found, meanwhile 2 other tables came in. Finally we got sat.

2.) I love to try new food and decided to try a new dish. I got 3/4 stars on spicy. My curry was just not good... I didn’t like it (it was flavorless, needed salt and seasoning, it wasn’t spicy AT ALL) I couldn’t keep eating it. I never send anything back but I had to let the server know. 
I told her I didn’t like the dish... 
to my surprised she responded that “it your decision to order that dish, and our policy is that we can’t take something off a bill because you simply didn’t like it” she left and came back and then let me know that she could give me a free spring roll but couldn’t take my food that I didn’t eat or like off the bill. 

3.) never seen a complaint handled this way in the service industry, it might not have been the servers fault but whoever implemented their policies needs to know they are going to lose customers if the customers concerns aren’t taken seriously.

name: Basil Leaf Restaurant
address: 235 Division St NW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews:
If I could leave less than one star I would. The food is decent at best which is the only semi-pleasant part of this dining experience. The customer service is genuinely horrible, the mess up my order constantly. The last time we went there we ordered “Pad See Ew” over the phone, when we arrived they had prepared the wrong food and when I told them it was wrong they literally would not make the correct order, over and over they said “just try it, you’ll like it.” Clearly just  they did not make the effort to correct their mistake. 
ZERO OUT OF TEN!

This shop has the best mom's pork fried rice in the world! And too top it off they also have the best and freshest fresh rolls I have ever had. And ive had at least a dozen from different resteraunts. The owners and employees are always very friendly fast and have never let me down after dining in and taking out for over 5 years.

polite service. they work hard and are working hard through the pandemic. even with some longer wait times then usual, greatly appreciated. tasty food! (one req, need more filling inside the crab rangoon. had a couple pieces with close to zero filling).

Had the giant prawns and was very happy with the crispy breading. Dipping sauce was sweet and tasty. Enjoyed the waitress who was learning English. If they had a more inspired music on the speakers it would have been even more enjoyable.
