Tasty meals, we all got lunch combo meals which were enough to fill us up (I'm a heavy eater). The single staff that we saw was very friendly and patient. The food was flavorful but a bit too salty/sweet and there was more oil than needed. Great spot in the area.

name: Pellegrinos Italian Kitchen & Catering
address: 205 Cleveland Ave SE, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Authentic & delicious! Seriously the best Italian restaurant I've ever been to. Not only were there huge portions (and I'm a big girl) but the food was so good. The ambience of the restaurant was very nice and cozy, intimate and romantic. All the staff were friendly and courteous.

I met a friend who is a business colleague after work for a social dinner at Pellegrinos Italian Kitchen & Catering in Tumwater.

Staying at the La Quinta Inn & Suites by Wyndham Tumwater - Olympia on Capitol Blvd SE, it was a super easy and quick drive to the restaurant.

Parking can be a little tight so I parked on the adjacent side-Street, Bates St SE. 
But this speaks to how popular and wonderful the restaurant really is!

My favorite types of restaurants are the local family-owned since you get that certain personal touch and atmosphere.

And Pellegrinos is definitely 5+ Stars!
The service was phenomenal and the food perfect.

I started out with the anti-pasta salad which I expected to be small but was more than generous loaded with all of the great stuff.

My meal was the veal parmigiana which couldn’t be made any better.
It was tender, tasty, and prepared just right. 
And the pasta and marinara sauce were excellent too.

This definitely a gem of a local restaurant.

Only reviews breakfast. Cinnamon roll was incredible, and I will absolutely be back for that, and for the excellent service! The potatoes and the Italian sausage were just right, and the lemon sauce on pancakes was exactly what I wanted. Friendly staff, not too long to wait between ordering and receiving food, and they made sure we liked everything we ordered.
First time here and it was great! Brought a friend for her birthday lunch. Delicious food and quick service.

This was the first time I had been to Pellegrinos. It's a cute place, with great food and excellent service. We were a party of 6 and were seated upstairs. So I would suggest if you have anyone in your party with diminished mobility, request a table on the main floor. Also, it was a little loud where we were seated. Not sure what that's like on the ground floor. Still, we will all go back for the food & service!

name: Ricardo's Kitchen + Bar
address: 676 Woodland Square Lp SE (Enter Off 7th), Lacey, WA 98503, USA
reviews:
I have been to numerous the nicest and well known steak restaurants in downtown Seattle and Bellevue area and there are only handful of them that are equivalent to Ricardo’s. 
Absolute hidden jewel in Olympia area.  You have to try their steak, it will blow your mind. 
For the lunch try 80-20 burger, for the dinner all of their steaks are cooked to perfection, and even plating(presentation) of the food is state of an art. Great selection of wine, great atmosphere. If you need to get a good steak in the area, look no further

My husband and I came here for our first time to celebrate my birthday and our anniversary. We had a reservation, and even though it was packed on a Saturday night and we were early for our reservation, we still got a table within 10 minutes.  We had the mushroom bruschetta for a starter, and it was so amazing, we ate every bite! I had the seafood tagliatelle for dinner, and my husband had the 14oz. 40-day rib eye. Everything was delicious! We were stuffed! And they offered me a complimentary dessert of my choice for my birthday. They also do military discount, which we appreciate. We will definitely be coming back and telling all of our friends about this place!

Ricardo's always delivers! This is becoming our go-to place for special occasions. It is pricey, but the amazing food and service more than compensate for that. The staff goes out of their way to ensure that their customers are completely satisfied each and every visit. We'll be back soon.

The food was awesome but the service was very poor. The waitress who was supposed to take my order acted like I wasn't there or would ask me for my order from the other side of the table. Other than the service, everything else was great.

We love it here!  They dry age their beef up to 50 days in house!  The dry aging room is visible right when you walk in! Amazing everything! They have a great wine selection and mix great cocktails!  A must try restaurant!

name: Quality Burrito
address: 213 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: This place was amazing!!!! The burrito we got was the grilled chicken ranchero and it was almost as big as the plate. It came with chicken, pickled jalapenos and carrots, rice, sour cream, guacamole, cheese and beans. Also we had ours fried which cost a dollar more but it was worth it!! One burrito is more than enough for 2 people. Will be going back again for sure!! So good!
First time at QB and I enjoy my dinner so much. Generous portion, tasty food, great service from both waiters, will definitely be back soon.
Wow.i mean wow.   Delicious burritos.   Very tasty.    First time being here and definitely will be back.     Just awesome.
Burrito?! Are you kidding?! These mothers are the greatest ever! Olympia is the place for burritos!

Already loved this place, and now found out that they've chosen to remove beef from their menu entirely due to environmental concers.

Major props, had to drop a 5 stars to counteract any salty carnivores

name: Great Cuisine of India
address: 116 4th Ave W, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: Very good restaurants... Liked the butter chicken best... Everything else was good except tandoori chicken which was little sweet. Will definitely try next time for other dishes

Solid menu, great price, AMAZING FLAVORS! Consistently good service and food quality. It’s always the exact same every time we visit. Two people can share one appetizer and an entree and be satisfied.

Had the buffet and it was decent but for me,   not something I'd repeat too soon. The meat was pretty dry and the samosa on the buffet was stuffed with rice and corn instead of the usual patatos,  peas,  etc.. so these two things really tainted my experience. Another fried item seemed stale - as if it sat on the buffet line too long.   Perhaps I caught them on an off day but I wasn't too pleased with that. The server was very nice and attentive with water and removing used dishes.  I just wanted the food to be better.

This is a family run restaurant, I had great Service and the food was very delicious. I got the "spicy" chicken Marsala which was hot for sure but had a great blend of flavors. Pair it with a beer and your good to go.

It was very good experience for us when we ate there. We were traveling from Portland to Seattle. We wanted to get some Indian food and this place was awesome! Customer service was good. We don’t have anything to complain! Several people asked us about the food in the restaurant. It was very easy to find perking since it was weekend. We ordered non vegetarian deal. It was plenty for both of us. I think three people can eat easily.

name: Dingey's
address: 700 Capitol Way N, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
Possibly the best food in Olympia. Limited hours and at the Farmers Market. 
So many ways to enjoy local oysters, and all made fresh on site.

I am a little suprised that the reviews are so good for this eatery.   It is not bad by any means, but in an area with tons of fresh good seafood, it also is not the top of the list either.  What this place does have is a good location.  As part of our outdoor Farmer's Market in the area, it is a hot food option while visiting the market.  I ordered the prawn basket and it was just ok.  If I were to return again I think I would try the crab cakes.  Just a so so place.
Excellent menu of northwest seafood delight with friendly staff serving behind the counter. Crab Cakes Benedict is delicious!
Pretty good choice if a little appetite plagues you. Great selection of fresh fish and seafood meals.
Dingey’s has the best clam chowder in the world and there fish and chips are incredible.

name: Swing Wine Bar
address: 825 Columbia St SW, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: We have always wanted to go here. A friend of ours invited us out.  Now we can't wait to go back. Excellent service, great food, excellent wine.  We were able to enjoy our friend and the food and not be interfered with for a long dinner.  We felt welcome and not out of place as some restaurants go if they can't turn the table over several times a night. I cannot wait to go back to continue going through their menu.

Swing Wine Bar is a cute, upscale yet homey feel, restaurant that overlooks the beautiful lake. The food is always devine, with well thought out menus. As a non drinker, they had crafty moktails, which were perfect! Large craft cocktail menu, with a great wine list as well! Perfect for any occasion, as they have outside AND inside seating. It's PERFECT FOR DATE NIGHTS.
Love getting dinner here. Fantastic location to bring a date or meet friends for dinner and drinks! Meals are exceptional!

Been here a couple times and have always had a great experience.  The ambiance is great - and old house overlooking Capital Lake converted into a wine bar restaurant.  Service is very attentive and friendly.  They have a happy hour menu called the Lush Rush that changes, not sure how often, but the drinks and food options change.   This visit was a happy hour visit with my mom and we both had a Five O'clock Somewhere drink, and the Bacon wrapped dates for a little bite to eat.   Both yummy!   Will continue to visit this little house on the hill!

Delicious food, must try the gorgonzola mushrooms, deviled eggs, street tacos were amazing. The baked brie is delicious as well. Huge menu of custom crafted cocktails and wine. You can also enjoy wine flights and whisky flights. The view is amazing, great service and atmosphere. Highly recommend.

name: Oly Rockfish Grill
address: 700 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews: This is the second poor review in a row for me. I used to love the goat cheese salad. Tonight the onions were way too pungent, the garlic wasn't cooked or sweet and the whole taste wasn't good. The waitress took forever to greet us. She was the only person I saw all night and she said it was her first night.

I'd give 6 stars if I could. Amazing food, outstanding service, beautiful venue, endless menu, this place was amazing. My friends/family from out of town demanded TO-GO boxes, & continued to talk about the food for hours afterward. Highly recommended!

We enjoyed a very yummy breakfast on Friday. I had the goat cheese & spinach scramble w/fruit & toast: FANTASTIC, delicious & not the typical boring & unripe fruit: a Wonderful, generous assemblage of delicious assorted fruit. My friends & I Will return!!
Got brunch and it was great! Chicken Fried Steak, a poached eggs, a biscuit, and grits! All flavorful and delicious! A decent Bloody Mary too.
Great breakfast spot, and has a cool lounge for cocktails in the evening with a decent dinner menu. Service was fast and professional.

name: Peppers Mexican Restaurant
address: 114 Cherry St NE, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews: I love the setting of old Mexico 🇲🇽. The food is just like home. I love the selection and the smells. The waitress is very courteous and funny. Food was prepared quick, hot and very tasty. Highly recommended.
Went there to have dinner tonight.  The place is empty and there's a sign in the window thanking customers for dining there for 28 years. But now they're closed for good.
Delicious food and drinks!! Love visiting peppers for the mole, but tried their crema sauce last night and wow was it good. They also deliver!
This was our first time at Peppers.  We stopped here for lunch.  The restaurant was nice and clean.  We ordered a chimichanga and fajitas.   The portions were large.  The food was great.

Although the food is generally pretty good, I am VERY concerned that several times I have received salsa that is so old that it is bubbling and fermenting. 

I hope that someone that works here is monitoring the feedback from customers - I order online often as I live close by, and feel I should be reimbursed fairly for at least two occasions I paid $4.99 for chips and salsa and gotten old batches. Also, I've gotten stale chips almost always. As an aside - if I were ordering in the restaurant, I wouldn't have to pay for chips and salsa at all, as its included in any Mexican restaurant. 

In general, these  mistake makes me worried that other things are also being overlooked, and I honestly want to keep being a customer... getting a little closer to not, though.

name: Falls Terrace Restaurant
address: 106 Deschutes Way SW, Tumwater, WA 98501, USA
reviews: I thoroughly enjoyed my meal here, to say the least. I got the sirloin steak with mashed potatoes and mixed squash and zucchini. The steak was a perfect medium rare. The restaurant is right along the falls and the view on a stormy night was incredible. This is my first night during a stay in Olympia and it was a wonderful way to start it!

Drove past the sign visable from I-5 near 101 for years.  Met Family there and were surprised that the view and food was even better than imagined.  Price was reasonable.   Parking out front on Deschutes was ample.  Bing Crosby's Great Grandfather's house further down the street.  Good Stop.
Delicious food, exceptional and kind service. First time visit for a special occasion... Will be back for more the next time we have someone to celebrate.
We go every Thanksgiving. Friendly staff, varied menu with delicious choices and a full bar!🙂

The food is beautifully presented and tastefully created. There are several healthy choices on the menu. Service is always top notch, and the view of the falls is spectacular. A bit on the pricey side, but worth the extra.

name: Equal Latin Restaurant & Bar
address: 520 4th Ave E, Olympia, WA 98501, USA
reviews:
This place has the most authentic Mexican food in town. The flavors are over the top! Great menu and very good table service. Chances are that the owner will stop by your table to ensure all is well.
The prices are moderate.
Generous servings for every plate I saw. A good selection of draft beers and a full bar.
This place is easy to find, access, and exit. It is fully handicapped accessable.
If you found this review to be helpful please consider adding a thumbs-up.

Had a wonderful dinner with my large group of friends - they accommodated us without issue and also got our entire order correct!  Delicious food with a spicy Latin twist. Self serve chips and salsa bar was fun and unique also! Happy hour menu and signature margarita- yummy! Definitely a great place and will come again!

I really enjoy this restaurant.  The owner is very friendly and the staff is nice.  I've been there a few times and the food is always delicious. I especially appreciate their salsa and salad bar. They also have a good selection of drinks.  I am always happy and satisfied with my visits.  I will definitely be returning. Thank you.

The food was fabulous and the prices were reasonable.  My group included a vegetarian who said the vegetarian/vegan menu was one of the most extensive in town. The serving sizes were immense, and the staff will bring to-go containers without being asked. There is both a salad bar and a chips and salsa bar that are complimentary. We were served by the owner, who was friendly, courteous, and patient with all our questions. I seldom leave reviews, but this place rocks -- try it!

nice place to go have a dinner,They have many options in Draft beer  And the menu they have so much options  And  Now they have vegetarian menu, Is very family oriented you can bring your kids.
 When I go to the restaurant I really want a cold beer and a good dinner and he called outings they have bought them I recommend this place to come over and try it.

name: IHOP
address: 3519 Martin Way E, Olympia, WA 98506, USA
reviews:
Will never order from this store again. Staff and manager not helpful when we had a problem with our order. Wanted to hand it off to someone else even though it wasn't door dashes fault our order was wrong and very cold.  The food where in plastic containers that had so much  condensation in them everything was soggy and wet. 
We just wanted to help the local businesses out in this time of need and enjoy a nice Sunday breakfast, but instead my husband spent his morning trying to get our order fixed and the kids ate cereal  
 next time I'll make our own breakfast
Cant go wrong here.    Always friendly staff and delicious food.  Great breakfast.
I've always loved it at IHOP watching my wife giggle about what devilishly sweet pancake plate she will have and the atmosphere is always light with friendly service.

The restaurant decor and condition of the furniture is better than other IHOPs restaurants in the area.  I ordered the Colorado Omelette, but it did not look near as appetizing as the picture on the menu. I'll try to order something different next time. I also had the side of fruit, 3 of 3 of the grapes in were not fresh. Learn from me, order something.  😉

EXCELLENT service by our waitress Lacy! Was very pleased with my savory crepes and my boyfriend got sweet strawberry crepes! Clean and cozy atmosphere, family friendly, and affordable. Will be back again!

name: Aya Sushi
address: 1540 Cooper Point Rd SW, Olympia, WA 98502, USA
reviews: Amazing sushi place! The staff is very polite, and my waiter even helped me decide what do order. Not only does it look beautiful, but tastes phenomenal. But, it does take some time for them to make it, so probably don't eat here if you have limited time.

My new favorite restaurant! Super tasty sushi and a great atmosphere for a really reasonable price! 
You can get a full plate of 7 to 10 pieces of delicious sushi for $10-15 — Fresh crab, tuna, shrimp, octopus, etc... 
Really, with how expensive seafood normally is at other restaurants, it amazing what you get. It's not a HUGE amount of food, but it's surprisingly filling and, more importantly, you feel great after eating! It has a refreshing and revitalizing aftereffect that you definitely don't get after eating a burger and fries at Red Robin.

I have avoided sushi my whole life. This is great. They have so many different rolls. One fills me up pretty well. My favorite is the Ichi Roll- tempura shrimp, avocado, cooked shrimp on top, cucumber & a sweet sesame dressing. It's in a strip mall, but the interior makes you feel like you are in a nice restaurant. Now I crave it every week. They also have American food as well as lots of other cooked dishes to try if raw isn't your thing.

Second or possibly third best sushi bar in Olympia after Sushi house and followed by Koibito which is only slightly behind. But still insanely good. Any of the top 3 would not be a wasted outing in the least.
I used to go here all the time before the virus and  Service is top notch and the food is amazing. The inside is beautiful and the lighting is calm.
